<SLUG> BC-Mexico-Chiapas, 1st Ld,0177 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Rebels, state police clash in Chiapas; at least one policeman dead
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with Chiapas governor raising death toll to nine. &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos pursuing &QL; 
 &UR; By ALEJANDRO RUIZ &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   SAN CRISTOBAL DE LAS CASAS, Mexico (AP) _ In one of the
deadliest clashes since the early days of the Zapatista uprising,
nine people were killed when the Army tried to retake control of a
town sympathetic to the rebels in the southern state of Chiapas.
Fifty-two people were arrested.
	   At least six of the victims in Wednesday's clash were believed
to be Zapatista rebels and one was a police officer. Gov. Roberto
Albores Guillen announced late Wednesday that two more people had
died, but didn't specify whether they were rebels or from the
security forces.
	   Earlier, the government had announced that nine people were
wounded, including seven police officers. One officer was wounded
when a police helicopter was fired on and forced to land.
 &UR; Peace talks, pickup 3rd graf previous
</TEXT>
