<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-APTV: 0600 Outlook,1222 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
STORY: 0600 Outlook     LENGTH:
RESTRICTIONS:     TYPE:

 &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  APTV 0600 OUTLOOK THURSDAY JUNE 11 1998  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 

 &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  For Planner / Newsdesk use - stories expected to move in the
next 12 hours. All times are GMT.  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
EXPECTED: &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
UN: DRUGS EUROPE - The UN's Drugs summit drew to a close on
Wednesday in New York, with a plan for governments to work together
to curb trafficking, demand, the illegal cultivation of narcotic
crops, improve judicial cooperation, and combat money-laundering by
2008. This wrap includes soundbites from the Dutch Foreign Minister,
Hans Van Mierlo, EU Commissioner Manuel Marin and Ruth Dreiffus,
Vice President of  Switzerland. (First run expected Europe Morning
0800)
----
PAKISTAN: BUDGET - Amid dire warnings the country is facing
financial collapse, Pakistan is to announce its budget for the 1999
fiscal year. Since the Islamic state was slapped with sanctions for
testing nuclear weapons last month, top Pakistani officials have
said the new budget will call for belt-tightening -- and probably
new taxes. APTV examines the pros and cons of such measures for the
country's impoverished population. (First run expected Asia Pacific
Late 0715)
---
JAPAN: FOOTBALL FANS - A group of Japanese World Cup fans were
bitterly disappointed on Thursday when they were told they wouldn't
be able to go to France to support their team in the World Cup. The
travel agents which organized their packages announced they didn't
have any tickets when the group turned up at the airport, ready to
fly. APTV has pictures of their protests. No Access Japan. (First
run expected Asia Pacific Late 0715)
----
HONG KONG: FINANCE - APTV will cover the Asian Financial Crisis
Conference where the Thai Deputy Premier will be giving a luncheon
address. (First run expected Asia Pacific Late 0715)
----
HONG KONG: GONG LI - Chinese actress Gong Li has received an award
from the French Consulate for her contribution to art and culture.
APTV will have pictures of the ceremony and file of Gong Li in
Cannes. (First run expected Asia Pacific Late 0715)
----
PHILIPPINES: ORCHESTRA - The prestigious New York Philharmonic
Orchestra is in the Philippines for the first time. It will perform
on Centennial day as part of the celebrations of the 100 anniversary
of the country's independence from Spanish rule. APTV follows the
166-person troupe and its 10-thousand kilos of cargo. (First run
expected Asia Pacific Late 0715)
----
PHILIPPINES: FARMERS  -  About 200 militant farmers have stormed a
government-run golf course in Manila and laid rice seedlings on the
10th hole in a protest to mark the 10th anniversary of the country's
land reform program. (First run expected Asia Pacific Late 0715)
----
THAI: ART -  Around 1,000 Thai works of art are due to be auctioned
off in Bangkok at knock-down prices over the weekend. 
They are the collected property of failed finance
companies, victims of the economic crisis, which seek to raise money
to repay their huge debts. APTV has pictures of the viewing. (First
run expected Asia Pacific Late 0715)
----
ARGENTINA: WRAP 2 -  Argentina's President Carlos Menem celebrated
the arrest of former president Jorge Videla on charges of child
kidnapping. (First Run Latin America 1900) The new cut includes one
more soundbite from the president of the Madres de Plaza de Mayo
movement. (First run 2130 Latin America) The new version will start
running from The Americas 0900.
----
NATO: KOSOVO  - APTV will cover the meeting of NATO defense
ministers in Brussels today (Thursday). They are expected to ponder
potential military options to halt ethnic carnage in Serbia's Kosovo
province. We expect to have their arrivals and start of meeting for
the Americas at 0900, then a package including a photo-opportunity
for Europe Late 1500 and NATO's secretary general Javier Solana's
press conference after 1600g. Our crews are also monitoring events
in Kosovo and the Albanian border.
----
IRAQ: BUTLER - We will also cover UN Chief Weapons Inspector Richard
Butler's arrival in Iraq today for a four-day mission. He is
returning to Baghdad for a new round of talks with Iraqi officials.
We expect to have pictures of him in time for Europe Late at 1500.
-----
