WORLD CUP: ROUND UP - APTV reports from Paris, Montpellier and
Glasgow on the reactions to the first two matches of the Football
World Cup. The pictures include soundbites from Scottish, Brazilian,
Norwegian and Moroccan supporters. (First run F-l-a-s-h 2315)
----
MEXICO: REBELS - APTV has pictures from Chiapas, where one police
officer was killed and unconfirmed reports said six rebels
supporters died during clashes. (First ran 0125 F-l-a-s-h) No Access
Mexico, CNN, Telenoticias, TV Azteca.
----
US: RACE KILLING 2 - A report from Jasper, Texas where authorities
say the death penalty is a possibility for three white Texan men
accused of dragging a black man to his death. Includes stills of the
suspects and the dead man, pictures of the crime scene and the truck
behind which victim James Byrd was allegedly dragged (First Ran
Europe Late 1500), a soundbite from Bill Clinton (First run
F-l-a-s-h 2315) and will be updated with comment from reverend
Jessie Jackson for Europe Early 0300.
-----
US:  SHOOTING -  The jury in the Mississippi school shooting trial
hears from student witnesses. Luke Woodham is accused of opening
fire at Pearl High last October, killing two classmates. No Access
Mississippi. (First Run F-l-a-s-h 0125)
----
UN: NETHERLANDS - APTV has the address of the Foreign Minister of
the Netherlands to the General Assembly. (First run Europe Early
0300)
----
UN: BILATERAL - APTV has pictures of the meeting between the German
Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel and his Iranian counterpart Kamal
Kharrazzi. (First run F-l-a-s-h 2315)
----
US: CHINA BABIES - Chinese dissident Harry Wu addresses a U-S
International Relations subcommittee hearing on abortion and
sterilisation in China. APTV has Wu's testimony in addition to
comments from the former administrator of China's Planned Birth
Control Office; a victim of coercive population control. (First Run
Australia/NZealand 0000)
----
BOSNIA: GOLDFISH - A Bosnian family who lost everything in the
recent war have been able to rebuild their lives -  thanks to
thousands of goldfish. Before fleeing the fighting, they threw the
contents of their fish tank into the village lake. Three years later
when they returned, the four fish had become thousands and a
profitable business. (First run  0300 Europe Early)
----
FRANCE: MANGETOUT - APTV has a feature on a French man who can eat
almost anything - from food to needles and glass - without digestion
problems. His biggest feat to date -- eating a Cessna plane and
landing a page in the Guinness Book of Records. (First run Europe
Early 0300)
