<HEADLINE>
Bell out for England
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ROTORUA, New Zealand (AP) _ A shoulder injury has delayed front
rower Duncan Bell's scheduled first appearance for England on
Saturday in the rugby union match against New Zealand A.
	   Sale loosehead prop Bell, 23, was withdrawn Thursday from the
touring side's opening match in New Zealand against the strong A
side at Hamilton after bruising his shoulder severely at training.
	   He will remain with the team following assurance by the
tourists' medical team the player would be fit to play by the end
of next week.
	   The front-row gap left by Bell will be filled by Tony Windo, a
late replacement on tour for injured test center Will Greenwood.
	   England coach Clive Woodward had decided an extra front rower
would be more useful for the team's five matches in New Zealand
than a midfield player. (djp)
