<HEADLINE>
Russia Central Bank reserves up to dlrs 15 billion
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The Russian Central Bank's gold and foreign
exchange reserves inched up dlrs 400 million last week, according
to a news agency report Thursday.
	   Reserves rose from dlrs 14.6 billion on May 29 to dlrs 15
billion on June 5, the Interfax news agency said.
	   The bank has been widely criticized for being too slow to raise
rates and spending its reserves when the first selling hit Russian
markets last fall.
	   Reserves fell from nearly dlrs 23 billion last summer to dlrs 18
billion at the beginning of this year. Analysts estimate the cash
reserves of the bank now hover around dlrs 10 billion.
	   (dj/ji) 	   
