<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Mayor Detained </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Mayor of Ukrainian city arrested for alleged criminal links
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) - A Ukrainian mayor has been detained for
alleged links with organized crime and is suspected of assisting a
gang that specialized in car theft, a newspaper said Thursday.
	   Prominent businessman Olexander Bushko became mayor of
Tsiurupynsk, about 600 kilometers (370 miles) south of Kiev, two
months ago. He was detained Wednesday by the regional police
organized crime department, Kievskiye Vedomosti said.
	   Bushko is suspected of serving as a middleman in negotiations
between the gang of car thieves and the stolen vehicles' owners,
the paper said. Car thieves in the former Soviet Union often sell
stolen cars back to their owners.
	   City residents were amazed by the arrest, since Bushko has been
active in forming municipal police units, to which he even donated
one of his own cars, Kievskiye Vedomosti said.
	   (sms/ji)
</TEXT>
