<HEADLINE>
Southern China executes 10 for murder, other crimes
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ Authorities in the southern city of Guangzhou
have executed 10 people convicted of murder, armed robbery or drug
trafficking, according to a report seen Thursday in Beijing.
	   The 10 were executed shortly after a public sentencing rally
held Wednesday to demonstrate the government's resolve to ``strike
hard'' at crime, the state-run newspaper Yangcheng Evening News
reported.
	   The report said seven of the 10 were found guilty of murder, but
it did not provide any further details.	   
