<HEADLINE>
Viagra pills disappear at Israeli parliament inquiry
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Some Israeli member of parliament just couldn't
restrain himself.
	   Samples of the Viagra anti-impotence pill disappeared at a
meeting of the parliamentary science committee on Wednesday,
causing great embarrassment among the doctors and other experts who
had been called to testify about whether the drug is safe or not.
	   The theft was discovered when committee chairwoman Dalia Itzik
asked if she could keep the box the pills came in, a committee
official told The Associated Press, speaking on condition of
anonymity.
	   Dr. Ami Sidi, an Israeli expert on impotence, opened the package
to empty it before handing it over, and found that only four of the
eight pills he had brought were left.
	   Shortly afterwards, the empty box also disappeared.
