<SLUG> BC-Greece-Teachers' Strike </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Striking teachers clash with riot police
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Striking teachers clashed with police
outside schools around Athens on Thursday, leaving at least one
person injured, authorities said.
	   The strikers were protesting new examinations introduced for
qualified teachers who wish to be appointed to state-run schools,
saying their university degrees should be the only qualification
necessary.
	   Under the previous system, teachers had to wait for years before
they received a state job.
	   Police used tear gas to push back protesters from a central
Athens high school, arresting three people.
	   Another two demonstrators were arrested and one police officer
suffered slight injuries when teachers attempted to occupy a school
in Pefki, a northern suburb, police said.
	   Teachers began a 48-hour strike to coincide with the start of
examinations on Friday, and have attempted to occupy schools where
they are set to take place in an effort to disrupt the tests.
	   Clashes between riot squads and teachers were also reported
outside at least one other Athens school.
	   (eb) 	   
