<SLUG> BC-Armenia-Bus Fire </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Death toll in Armenian bus fire rises to four
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   YEREVAN, Armenia (AP) _ A teacher and a schoolgirl died of heavy
burns on Thursday, bringing the death toll from the weekend bus
fire in Armenia to four, officials said Thursday.
	   Ripsime Khachatrian, 43, and Anna Oganesian, 13, died in the
Yerevan Central Hospital, hospital officials said. Two schoolboys
died in the same clinic earlier this week.
	   More than 20 schoolchildren were badly burned when their bus,
carrying 40 students, teachers and parents returning from a picnic,
exploded Sunday on a country road near the village of Bartsrashen,
30 kilometers (19 miles) south of Yerevan.
	   Officials said the explosion was apparently caused by a gas
leak.
	   Most buses and other vehicles in Armenia run on natural gas.
Gasoline is in short supply due to an economic blockade imposed by
neighboring Azerbaijan because of the two countries' territorial
conflict over Nagorno-Karabakh.
	   Several other victims remain in grave condition, said Norair
Davidian, Armenia's top burn-treatment expert.
	   (str/vi/ji) 	   
