<HEADLINE>
Monarchs coach Lionel Taylor resigns
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Lionel Taylor, the all-time leading receiver in
Denver Broncos' history, has resigned as the coach of the England
Monarchs after a 3-7 season, the team announced Thursday.
	   The losing season was the fifth straight for the Monarchs in NFL
Europe, the league's developmental and promotional arm on the
continent.
	   Taylor joined the Monarchs as an offensive coordinator in 1995
and moved up to head coach two games into the 1996 season.
	   ``I have enjoyed my time with the Monarchs, even though I have
been disappointed at our results on the field,'' he said. ``I felt
it was best for me and the team to make a change.''
	   In addition to his years with the Broncos, Taylor was also an
offensive assistant on two Pittsburgh Steelers teams that won Super
Bowls.
