<SLUG> BC-Israel-Building Collapse,0136 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Two teenagers killed as gym roof collapses on basketball team
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Two Israeli teen-age boys were killed when the
roof of their high school gym collapsed during a basketball game in
the southern city of Beersheba, officials said Thursday.
	   The roof of the Makif Vav high school caved in Wednesday
evening. Thirteen boys managed to get out safely but the bodies of
Lior Kavalo, 13, and Shlomi Toledo, 14, were recovered Thursday
after firefighters and army engineers cleared the rubble.
	   The roof was being repaired because it leaked, Beersheba Mayor
David Bonfeld told Israel radio, and 22 tons of concrete had been
poured onto it. Police questioned six people including the engineer
responsible for the work, the radio reported.
