<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Norway-Perky Prisoner </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Prisoner on jogging tour leaves his guards in the dust
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   OSLO, Norway (AP) _ A Norwegian prison inmate allowed to go
jogging with four of his guards turned out to be in pretty good
shape. Too good, in fact.
	   When the small entourage reached a recreation area outside the
prison in the northern town of Bodoe, the prisoner picked up the
pace, pulled ahead of his guards and escaped, the Norwegian news
agency NTB reported on Thursday.
	   The prisoner, identified only as a man in his late 20s, had been
jailed for petty crimes, and as trustee had been granted special
privileges, including excursions outside the prison, the report
said.
	   The escapee can expect to have his privileges revoked, assuming,
of course, that police manage to catch him.
	   (dm-jd)
</TEXT>
