<SLUG> BC-Palestinian-CIA </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CIA chief meets Arafat and top security officers in Gaza
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By SAMAR ASSAD &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ CIA Director George Tenet discussed a U.S
proposal for an Israeli troop withdrawal with Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat and his senior security advisers, a Palestinian
official said Thursday.
	   The official, who attended Wednesday night's meeting in Gaza,
told The Associated Press that Tenet's meeting with the
Palestinians was part of his visit to the region which included
stops in Israel, Jordan and Egypt.
	   Richard Scorza, spokesman for the U.S. Embassy in Tel Aviv
declined comment on the report, also broadcast by Israel Radio.
	   The official, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the talks
touched generally on the stalled peace process between Israel and
the Palestinians and involved a review of a U.S. proposal for
Israel to withdraw from 13.1 percent from the West Bank.
	   The official declined to say if specific arrangements for the
withdrawal were discussed.
	   Since the breakdown in talks more than a year ago, the CIA has
acted as a catalyst for Israeli-Palestinian cooperation on security
issues.
