<HEADLINE>
Sabena tries out new luggage service
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) - Belgium's national airline, Sabena,
said Thursday it was testing a new service that picks up a
passenger's luggage from home or hotel 24 hours ahead of a flight.
	   The service is in response ``to the numerous clients who seek
more speed and flexibility,'' the airline said in a statement.
	   With the ``Home Advanced Check-In'' service customers get their
boarding passes in advance rendering an airport check-in
unnecessary.
	   The airline promises the luggage will be on the appropriate
flight. The service costs 1,500 francs (dlrs 40) in case of a
luggage pick-up from a hotel, and 2,000 francs (dlrs 55) from home.
