<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-World Cup-Betting </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Six figure World Cup wager on Bulgaria
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ A 100,000-pound (dlrs 164,000) bet on Bulgaria to
beat Paraguay on Friday was the first six-figure wager on a single
World Cup game placed in Britain, bookmakers William Hill said
Thursday.
	   William Hill, which offered odds of 6-5 on Bulgaria beating
Paraguay, said a man placed the bet over the telephone from the
Mediterranean.
	   The man stands to win 120,000 pounds (dlrs 197,000) if Bulgaria
wins Friday, but his stake has dragged the odds on the team winning
the game down to even money.
	   A Paraguay win was offered at 12-5 and a draw at 2-1.
	   William Hill spokesman Graham Sharpe said the first six-figure
bet on the tournament was a 120,000-pound (dlrs 197,000) wager on
the Netherlands winning the World Cup.
	   ``We're anticipating an industry betting turnover of more than
100 million pounds (dlrs 164 million) on the World Cup, and wagers
like these are already making that look a conservative estimate,''
he said.
	   Paraguay goalkeeper Jose Luis Chilavert, who also takes his
team's penalty kicks and free kicks, has attracted bets at 1,000-1
to be the World Cup's leading goal scorer.
	   (jp) 	   
</TEXT>
