<HEADLINE>
Man injured in collision of train with truck dies
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ A 59-year-old man died in hospital
early Thursday of injuries sustained in a train accident, media
reported.
	   The man was seriously injured Wednesday, when a truck collided
with a passenger train at a railway crossing near Blatenka, some
100 kilometers (62 miles) southwest of Prague, CTK news agency
said.
	   Another 14 people were injured in the crash, one of them _ a
woman traveling in the truck _ seriously. The man who died was a
passenger on the train.
	   The truck was speeding when it struck the train, police said,
causing the accident.
	   According to CTK, the crossing did not have warning light
signals.
