<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Israel-Australia </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Israel's parliament unlikely to probe bridge disaster
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By MASHA HERBST &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer
said Thursday it appeared Israel's parliament did not plan to
investigate the Maccabiah bridge collapse which claimed the lives
of four Australian athletes last year.
	   Alexander made the comment to reporters after meeting with
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who was non-committal
about an independent probe by parliament that has been proposed by
the families of victims.
	   ``I didn't get the impression in my discussions with the Prime
Minister that he was on the verge of establishing a parliamentary
investigation,'' Downer told reporters.
	   A government-appointed panel of engineers looked into the cause
of the collapse, which occurred during the Maccabiah games, an
Olympic-style competition that gathered Jewish athletes from around
the world.
	   The panel issued a scathing report that blamed the builders and
organizers, and a police investigation led to the trial currently
underway in Tel Aviv of five people including the bridge's engineer
and two contractors.
	   Netanyahu, who plans a trip to Australia in August, promised to
finish looking into the matter before he arrived, but left unclear
whether he would agree to demands for compensation for the families
of victims.
	   ``By the time I get to Australia, I'm sure we will have
completed our examination,'' Netanyahu told reporters.
	   Netanyahu described the bridge collapse as a tragedy and said
that while Israel had ``done a few things, it can do more, and we
have to do more.''
	   ``What we intend to do is plan to give as much ... assistance to
the families, to the victims of this tragedy, as we can.''
	   Downer told reporters that he believed Israel should sign the
Nuclear Non-proliferation Treaty, but he said the issue did not
come up in 45-minute meeting at the Prime Ministry.
 &UR; mh-nbt 	   
