<SLUG> BC-Sports-Golf-Suntory Ladies </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
McGuire takes first round lead
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KOBE, Japan (AP) _ Marnie McGuire of New Zealand shot a
four-under-par 68 Thursday and took the one-stroke first round lead
in the 50 million yen (dlrs 352,000) Suntory Ladies Open golf
tournament.
	   The 29-year-old McGuire, winner of the 1986 All England Women
amateur championships, carded six birdies and two bogeys on the
6,346-yard, par-72, Arima Royal Golf Club course in Kobe, western
Japan.
	   ``I could play well today. My putting was particularly good,''
said McGuire, who won four Japan LPGA tournaments in the past four
years.
	   One stroke behind McGuire at 69 were two Japanese _ veteran
Nayoko Yoshikawa and Keiko Suzuki.
	   Ayako Shibata of Japan shot 70 and placed fourth.
	   Ai-sook Kim and Young-mee Lee, both of South Korea, shot 71s and
tied with eight Japanese for fifth place.
	   A total of 132 golfers, including 12 non-Japanese teed off in
cloudy weather.
	   Kaori Hara of Japan, who leads the money earning list with two
victories this season, shot 74 and tied 43th place with 12 other
Japanese.
	   The winner will pocket 9 million yen (dlrs 63,000).
 &UR; (sk) 	   
