<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Czech-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Drug traffickers arrested
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ Police arrested two German
nationals early Thursday on charges of drug trafficking and seized
thousands of shots of cocaine, police officials said.
	   The two men are suspected of heading an international ring that
smuggles drugs between Brazil and Germany, said Ivana Moosova, a
police spokeswoman in Prague. One of the men was arrested in
Germany and the other in a Prague hotel.
	   Moosova said 4,000 shots of cocaine were seized in the hotel
room, each weighing from 0.5 to 1 gram. The cocaine was meant to
test the market in the Czech Republic, where addicts have
multiplied almost threefold in the past five years, police
officials said.
	   In 1997, police arrested 130 people _ 29 of them foreigners _ on
drug-related charges and seized drugs worth more than 1 billion
koruna (dlrs 28.5 million), according to Jiri Komorous, head of the
Czech anti-narcotics squad.
	   Moosova said the 42-year-old man arrested in Prague, whom she
identified only as J. G., will be extradited to Germany.
	   (nr/me)
</TEXT>
