<HEADLINE>
Drainage work to end floods, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Drainage work to end floods, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   FLOOD woes in Taman Sri Muda, Shah Alam will hopefully be a
thing of the past when flood mitigation programmes, jointly
undertaken by the Shah Alam Municipal Council and the Drainange and
Irrigation Department, are completed in September.
	   Council president Mohammad Adzib Mohd Isa said the first and
second phases of the project were completed last year.
	   ``The tidal gate which was completed last September has improved
the flood situation in Taman Sri Muda significantly,'' he said.
	   He said the third phase, which included the contruction of large
and small drains and retention ponds, was under the Selangor DID.
	   The first phase costs the council RM12.4 million while the
second phase, costing RM15 million, involves the construction of
additional bunds along main drains to prevent water from the river
entering the housing estate during high tide.
	   Speaking to reporters after the handing over of a clock tower in
Section 15 by the UMW Group to the council, Mohammad Adzib said the
council was going all out to prepare for the Commonwealth Games in
September.
	   He said the council received RM3 million from the Landscaping
Department to beautify Shah Alam for the event.
	   ``We are topping up that amount with another RM3 million to
ensure that the venues for the boxing and cycling events are not
only ready but presentable and up to standard.''
	   He said three major companies have also made contributions by
way of building monuments for the games.
	   
</TEXT>
