	   KEMAYAN Advance Tertiary College is offering a programme leading
to the Bachelor of Jurisprudence degree awarded by University of
Malaya.
	   Kemayan ATC has been conducting this programme since September
1997.
	   The college is having an intensive revision programme for
students taking the September examinations on weekends for 10
weeks, commencing on June 27, course adviser Santhi Latha said.
	   ``The revision programme will emphasise the past year
examination questions and answering techniques,'' Santhi said.
	   ``Revision is important for the students as it is an opportunity
for them to gain an overview of the subjects.''
	   On Saturdays, it will be from 2pm to 9pm and on Sundays from
10am to 7.45pm.
	   She said the time-table was carefully structured to make it
convenient for students who come from all over the country.
	   To further assist students, Kemayan ATC plans to conduct a Final
Analysis Session about two weeks before the examinations. The
weekend session will focus on seven or eight of the most commonly
examined topics.
	   Seats are limited and interested students are required to book
their places.
	   For more information, visit Kemayan ATC at Bangunan Tunas Utama,
off Jalan Petaling, 50000 Kuala Lumpur or call 03-2010266 or fax
03-2010261.
	   
