For quality Engineering programme, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SINCE it was set up in January 1985, Kolej Damansara Utama's
School of Engineering has seen more than 2,000 of its students
graduate.
	   ``Our 13-year proven track record attests to the quality of our
programmes,'' said its dean Choong Khong Min.
	   The school specialises in Electronics, Computer, Electrical and
Telecommunications studies.
	   Its programmes include the KDU graduate diploma/University of
Lincolnshire and Humberside Bachelor of Engineering (Hons) in
Electronic and Electrical Engineering.
	   ``This unique programme, which was started in 1990, is a
home-grown course developed by KDU,'' said Choong.
	   Among its special features is that graduates get three
qualifications in one programme.
	   ``Besides the KDU graduate diploma and ULH degree, students also
acquire professional qualifications from the Engineering Council,
Britain,'' added Choong.
	   All three years of the course are done at KDU, which works out
to substantial savings of up to RM150,000.
	   The course also includes a component in industrial training -
something that is rare among local private colleges, said Choong.
	   ``Industrial training is important as it provides exposure for
students in a real working environment,'' he added.
	   Entry requirements to the KDU diploma include SPM, GCE O-level
or equivalent qualifications.
	   For the ULH degree, entry requirements into Year One are the KDU
Foundation in Science and Engineering, STPM, GCE A-evel or other
equivalent qualifications.
	   With KDU's Diploma in Engineering or other recognised equivalent
qualifications, students gain entry directly into Year Two of the
ULH programme.
	   Three are three intakes yearly, with the next one commencing on
Aug 24.
	   For details, call 03-7188123 or fax 7166029. The e-mail address
is info &LR; kdu.edu.my
	   
</TEXT>
