AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   WITHIN two years of its founding in 1991, Brickfields College
moved from its rented premises to its own buildings.
	   Its colleges are fully equipped with a library which can
accommodate 120 students, state-of-the-art computer laboratories
and other facilities.
	   Its director of studies, Jothi Ram, said Brickfields started
with three courses offering the Certificate of Legal Practice, LLB
and A-level.
	   It now offers a wide range of courses including the NCC
International Diploma in Computer Science from the National
Computing Centre, United Kingdom.
	   Ram said students intending to do a degree in Computer Science
can now do so locally - getting their NCC diploma in the first year
followed by the higher diploma in the second year and the degree in
the third.
	   Students will be awarded the BSc (Hons) in Computing and
Information Systems from the London Guildhall University.
	   Bricfields College also offers the Diploma in Business Studies
from the Association of Business Executives (ABE, UK).
	   Jothi said Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia students are required to sit
for the Brickfields Business certificate before going into the
one-year diploma programme.
	   Upon completion of the diploma, students can pursue their ABE
Advanced Diploma.
	   From there, the diploma holders can gain entry into the third
year of degree programmes in Business Studies or Business
Administration in selected universities in the UK, Australia and
New Zealand. It also serves as an entry qualification for MBA
programmes.
	   The college is also conducting courses for the Chartered
Institute of Marketing.
	   Brickfields College is also offering the MBA in collaboration
with Sheffield Hallam University (SHU), UK.
	   Ram said the college was scheduled to start a number of distance
learning programmes which will be offered via the Internet late
this year or early next year.
	   For details, call 03-2744256 or fax 03-2744174, or visit the
college at 80-82 Jalan Tun Sambanthan, Kuala Lumpur.
	   
</TEXT>
