	   KEMAYAN Advance Tertiary College is offering two professional
courses for those keen on a career in accountancy.
	   These are the Association of Chartered Certified Accountants and
the Chartered Institute of Management Accountants.
	   In 1997, the ACCA introduced the Accounting Technicians course
as a support to produce qualified personnel to assist accountants.
	   Accounting technicians are exempted from the foundation stage of
the ACCA course.
	   The ACCA qualification is acceptable for membership with the
Malaysian Institute of Accountants and this is essential for all
those who intend to practise as public accountants.
	   There are numerous career opportunities for ACCA graduates
including as accountants, management consultants and tax
consultants.
	   The CIMA qualification and the ACCA are both regarded as
equivalent to an honours degree. Holders of these qualifications
are eligible for membership with the MIA.
	   The current examination format of the CIMA course has also been
made modular.
	   Kemayan ATC places great emphasis on the quality of teaching and
its team of lecturers are highly competent and experienced in their
own field of specialisation.
	   Its facilities include a well-stocked library with the latest
reference materials.
	   ``Our team of experienced and proven lecturers are dedicated to
provide the right training to students for them to approach the
examinations confidently in their pursuit of educational
excellence,'' Kemayan ATC's Business School coordinator Clement
Thangam said.
	   Kemayan ATC is located at Bangunan Tunas Utama, off Jalan
Petaling, 50000 Kuala Lumpur. For more information, call 03-2010266
or fax 03- 2010261.
	   
