<HEADLINE>
Strategic location and links with top universities, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Strategic location and links with top universities, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Annie Freeda CruezASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SEPANG Institute of Technology, strategically located at Klang
Parade in Klang, is a premier learning institution having links
with some of the world's best universities.
	   The evolution of SIT has been distinguished by the quality,
commitment and enthusiasm of its staff who are highly qualified
academicians and industry professionals.
	   Visiting professors and academicians from leading international
universities ensure quality is never sacrificed.
	   The state-of-the-art facilities in SIT include a Learning
Resource Centre, a computer centre, language laboratories, 58
lecture rooms, 28 tutorial rooms, 11 engineering and science
laboratories, a modern auditorium which has a capacity to
accommodate 300 people and a 200-seat conference hall.
	   Students also receive a wide range of support services including
help to get accommodation, transportation, career and psychological
counselling.
	   The programmes offered at SIT range from pre-university
programmes, diploma courses, undergraduate programmes to
postgraduate programmes and professional courses.
	   The pre-university programmes consist of SIT's Degree Foundation
Studies, Cambridge A-level and South Australian Matriculation. The
DFS programme is accepted by 18 universities in the United Kingdom
and 17 in Australia.
	   Among universities SIT has ties with are the University of
Adelaide, University of South Australia, The Northern Consortium of
Universities UK, University of London and Oxford Brookes
University.
	   Among programmes offered are the University of London (External
Programme)'s Bachelor of Science.
	   An American Degree Programme at the institute offers Bachelor of
Science in Business and Engineering with four universities in the
US while the Bachelor of Arts (Hons) in Business Administration is
awarded by the University of Huddersfield, United Kingdom.
	   SIT also offers diploma courses in Business, Computer and
Information Science, and Engineering, SIT Advanced Diploma in
Information Technology.
	   Professional courses are also offered besides two postgraduate
programmes, a Master in Business Administration from the University
of South Australia and two Master's of Science courses from the
University of East London.
	   
