<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Israel-Where's the Viagra?,0134 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Viagra pills disappear at Israeli parliament inquiry
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ It's hard to keep a good pill around.
	   Samples of the Viagra impotence drug disappeared at a meeting of
an Israeli parliamentary science committee on Wednesday,
embarrassing doctors and other experts who had been called to
testify about the drug's safety.
	   The theft was discovered when committee chairwoman Dalia Itzik
asked if she could keep the box the pills came in, a committee
official told The Associated Press on condition of anonymity.
	   Dr. Ami Sidi, an Israeli expert on impotence, opened the package
to empty it before handing it over, and found that only four of the
eight pills he had brought were left.
	   Shortly afterwards, the empty box also disappeared. 	   
