	   SIXTY-seven teachers from 31 secondary schools in the Klang
District attended the half-day Introductory NIE Workshop at Sekolah
Menengah Kebangsaan Perempuan Bukit Kuda, Klang on May 23.
	   The workshop was organised by the New Straits Times with the
support and cooperation of SMK (P) Bukit Kuda, whose principal
Hajah Habsah Abd Rahman is the chairperson of the English Language
Curriculum Committee for Klang District.
	   All the workshops are fully sponsored by the New Straits Times
which finances tea and lunch for the participants, supplies
newspapers, provides files and handouts, and awards prizes for the
hands-on activities.
	   Participants also take home magazines as souvenirs and
certificates of attendance.
	   Teachers are not charged a fee for attending the NIE workshop.
	   The New Straits Times would like to thank the principal of SMK
(P) Bukit Kuda for allowing the school to be used as the venue and
members of the school's English language department for helping
out.
