	   IPOH, Tues. - The Lions Club of Kinta today conferred its
highest award, the Melvin Jones Fellow, on the Raja Permaisuri of
Perak Tuanku Bainun.
	   The Melvin Jones Fellow, named after the founder of Lions
International, is an award accorded to recipients in recognition of
their humanitarian contribution to society.
	   Tuanku Bainun received the award from District 308-B governor
Allan Cheah.
	   The Sultan of Perak Sultan Azlan Shah was present at the
ceremony.
	   In conjunction with the award ceremony, the club hosted a high
tea for more than 100 children from orphanages and charitable
bodies at the Syuen Hotel.
	   Later, awards recognising the contributions of Lions Club
members were given out. There was also a cake-cutting ceremony in
honour of Sultan Azlan Shah's recent birthday.
	   
