	   TENS of thousands of entries have been received for the
Coca-Cola World Cup promotion which offers passionate football fans
an all-expenses paid trip for two for the rest of his or her life
to future World Cup finals.
	   Entries for the ``Coca-Cola I'm A Fan'' promotion launched four
weeks ago offers the biggest prize a soccer fan can ever ask for.
	   Coca-Cola brand manager Winnie Khor said about 5,700 entries
have been received and the company anticipates the number to
increase substantially once World Cup '98 kicks off today.
	   ``The hardcore soccer fans are patiently waiting to assess the
form of the participating teams before they decide on the team they
think will win the world's most prestigious sports event.
	   ``We are pleased with the response especially in the light of
many other promotions being held simultaneously and will reward the
first 100,000 early birds with a range of Coca-Cola collectibles,''
said Khor.
	   She added that besides the two air tickets, airfare plus
expenses to watch the World Cup finals for life from 2002, the
first prize winner will also receive RM10,000 and a World Cup '98
winner's jersey.
	   The second, third, fourth and fifth prize winners will get
RM5,000, RM3,000, RM1,500 and RM1,000 cash respectively, a World
Cup '98 winner's jersey and exclusive Coca-Cola gear.
	   Coca-Cola, a major sponsor of France World Cup '98 and official
drink for the event, held similar promotions around the globe.
	   ``Four talented Malaysian schoolboys have also been selected to
represent the country in a Coca-Cola pre-match curtain raiser on
June 26 at the Stade d'France,'' said Khor.
	   
</TEXT>
