	   PAY a visit to City Villa Hotel Kuala Lumpur (formerly Asia
Hotel) anytime until Aug 3 and let the hotel staff pamper you.
	   The hotel launched its ``Let Us Manja U'' campaign for the third
year running recently, with the opening of Antara Holiday Villa's
first hotel at Cherating in Pahang.
	   The launching was officiated by Antara chairman Azman Shah Haron
in the presence of City Villa managing director Ahmad Kamal
Merican.
	   Hotel resident manager Suraya Ariffin said the campaign was a
sort of quality service assurance practised by all Antara hotel
subsidiaries.
	   She said it was an annual event but the campaign period differed
from one hotel to another.
	   She said the acronym Manja stands for Must smile and be
courteous, Anticipate our customers needs, Never forget that
customers are No 1, Just ensure that there is a detailed follow-up
and always give our personal attention.
	   During the period, staff will have to follow a manual that has
been prepared by the management.
	   ``Within these two months our customers are given the chance to
nominate their favourite staff from the `front of the house', which
includes front office and coffeehouse, and the `back of the house'
comprising housekeeping, security and administration departments.
	   Suraya said winning staff will be treated to a seven-day cross
exposure training stint at any of the Antara Holiday Villa chain
hotels in the country with all expenses paid.
	   In addition, they will also receive a plaque, souvenir and
certificate each.
	   In conjunction with the launching of the Manja campaign, City
Villa presented awards to its best employees from various
department. They were Rostam Jamaludin, Normala Hassan, Yong Oi
Mian, Sabari Abdul Hamid, Hasniro Hasbullah, Ravi Nagappan and Samy
Sinnan.
	   Twenty-eight employees whose birthdays fell between April and
June were also feted.
	   
