	   KOTA BARU, Tues. - The State Immigration Department has rounded
up 28 Thais, including eight women, for working in the State
illegally.
	   The department also detained five locals for allegedly
harbouring the foreigners.
	   Its enforcement chief Zakaria Husin said the foreigners were
between the ages of 17 and 34.
	   ``The Thais were working at food stalls in Jalan Kubang Kerian,
Panji and Parit Dalam while the locals are the owners.''
	   He said 15 officers led by the department director Kamaluddin
Amah raided the places after receiving a tip-off.
	   
