BRUSSELS: NATO 2 - APTV has a crew covering the meeting of NATO
defense ministers in Brussels to discuss ways of ending the carnage
in Kosovo. The existing arrivals package (see below) will be updated
with a photo-opportunity (Europe Late 1500) and comment from NATO's
secretary general Javier Solana and US Defense Secretary William
Cohen. (After 1600g).
----
US: S.KOREA - APTV is following the South Korean President on his
visit in Washington. On Thursday, after a breakfast meeting with
Bill Clinton Kim Dae-jung will meet IMF officials and then depart
for California. (1500 Europe Late)
----
ERITREA: BORDER - APTV will have latest pictures of the tense
Eritrea/Ethiopia border region, where fighting has been taking
place. (1500 Europe Late)
----
WORLD CUP: FESTIVAL - The host city of Lyons prepares for World
Cup matches by holding Mexican and Colombian cultural celebrations.
(2130 Latin America Late)
----
ALBANIA: REFUGEES - APTV is chasing pictures from the Albanian
border with Kosovo, as the tide of refugees from the province
continues. (1500 Europe Late)
----
IRAQ: BUTLER - APTV's package is set to shows the news conference by
the UN chief weapons inspector, Richard Butler, and will include
general views of Baghdad and shots of leading Iraqi newspaper which
has called on Iraq not to comply with the UN. (1500 Europe Late)
----
US: CHINA - Two weeks away from his China trip, President Bill Clinton
will use a speech to the National Geographic Society in Washington
to defend himself against criticism of the visit. (1830 North
America)
----
RUNNING:  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
