<HEADLINE>
Hasina goes to Delhi, Islamabad June 16, 24, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Hasina goes to Delhi, Islamabad June 16, 24, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina will visit both India and Pakistan
within next two weeks, a top official of the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs said here last night.
	   Foreign Secretary Mustafizur Rahman told the BSS that the
Bangladesh leader held telephone conversation with Pakistan Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif last evening. She will visit Pakistan on June
24.
	   Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, who had telephoned Indian Prime
Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee yesterday evening, will go to New
Delhi on June 16, Rahman said.
	   Rahman said both the visits will be brief and the Prime Minister
will return home on the same days.
	   The Foreign Secretary informed that the Pakistan visit is being
little delayed as Nawaz Sharif will be on a visit outside the
country from June 13 to June 20, he added.
	   Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina expressed her desire to visit India
and Pakistan in separate letters addressed to their leaders in the
aftermath of nuclear tests carried out by both the countries that
created tension in the region. In her letter to the two leaders,
Sheikh Hasina expressed her desire to discuss with them the matters
of mutual interest and other issues.
	   The letters were handed over to the High Commissioners of the
two countries a couple of days ago.
	   
</TEXT>
