	   A 15-year agreement for power purchase by installing a 100 MW
barge-mounted plant at Baghabari in Serajgonj district was accorded
in Dhaka yesterday between Bangladesh Power Development Board
(BPDB) and Westmont Power (Bangladesh) Pvt Ltd. This is the fourth
agreement of this kind in the country.
	   Under the agreement Westmont Power (Bangladesh) Pvt Ltd, an
associate of Westmont Offshore (Malaysia), will install and
commission the barge-mounted power plant within three months of
signing the agreement.
	   The capacity of the plant will rise to 130 MW after 15 months of
commercial operation following conversion of the plant into a
combined cycle.
	   Nuruddin M Kamal, Chairman, BPDB and Sio Kai Sing, Managing
Director, Westmont Power (Bangladesh) Pvt Ltd signed the agreement
on behalf of their respective organisations.
	   
