	   KUALA LUMPUR, Tues. - Ikan merah was more expensive today, with
the Chow Kit wet market offering the best bargain at RM9 per
kilogramme.
	   Green chillies were cheapest at the Petaling Jaya Old Town wet
market at RM5 per kg, while Lucky Garden topped the list at RM18
per kg.
	   Cucumbers were sold for RM1.19 per kg at Carrefour, while sawi
went for RM2.79 at the Giant hypermarket in USJ - cheaper by 71 sen
compared to last Thursday's price.
	   In Ipoh, prices of essential food items remained stable today.
	   Ikan bawal hitam was sold between a reasonable RM12 and RM15.90
per kg at all outlets surveyed, while the cheapest cencaru could be
found at Jaya Jusco at RM4.90 per kg.
	   Spinach was slightly expensive at the Canning Garden market,
retailing for RM3.50 per kg, while it was going for RM2.70 at the
Central market.
	   Other items such as dried chillies, potatoes and long beans,
were also priced reasonably. In Johor Baru, there was an increase
in the prices of certain essential items sold in the supermarkets
surveyed.
	   Tops was selling ikan merah at RM23.90 per kg, an increase of
RM10 per kg as compared to last week.
	   There was also an increase in the prices of ikan selar, brinjal
and sawi. However, Tops had the cheapest Labour brand cooking oil.
	   
