<HEADLINE>
New industrial policy to be announced soon, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
New industrial policy to be announced soon, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Industries Minister Tofail Ahmed yesterday informed in
Parliament that a new industrial policy will be announced soon
envisaging measures to match with the free-market economy.
	   He said the government will privatise all the profitable and
loosing units of public sector in phases to operate in competition
in the free market.
	   Replying to Master Mujibur Rahman (AL) during the question hour,
the minister said 54 textile, jute, steel, sugar, chemical,
forestry and other sectors have been identified to sell out during
the current fiscal year.
	   The process is underway either to close down or sell the loosing
public sector mills and factories.
	   Till December 97, he said, 11 mills of textile sector were
closed down and their workers off loaded under the voluntary
retirement programme by giving them all financial benefits.
	   The Industries Minister presented a list of public sector mills
and factories with year wise financial loss incurred since the
nationalisation.
	   
</TEXT>
