	   SOME 300 students from 42 universities and colleges in 11
countries participated in the Fifth All-Asian Inter-varsity English
Debating Championship held in Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia in
Bangi recently.
	   The competition, with the theme Asia With Attitude, was
organised by the UKM Debate Society and UKM Students Union.
	   Eight participants from the Philippines were in the list of Top
Ten debaters, with the remaining two places going to students of
Universiti Malaya and the National University of Singapore.
	   Among the Filipino winners were Gerardo Laragoza and Praba
Ganesan from De La Salle University; Franco Aristotle Larcina,
Arlene Maneja and Rudi Ramin from University of Santo Tomas;
Michelle Marie De Guzman from Assumption College, and Ana Analo
from University of Philippines Deliman.
	   Also making it to the Top Ten were S. Chandran from Universiti
Malaya and Kunal M. Joshi from NUS.
	   Present on the fifth and final night and prize presentation was
the Yang di-Pertuan Agong Tuanku Ja'afar, who performed the
official closing ceremony.
	   On hand to receive the King was competition patron, UKM deputy
vice- chancellor Prof Datuk Dr Anwar Ali.
	   Among the participating countries were Bangladesh, Thailand,
Japan, Indonesia, India and South Korea.
	   The local institutions which took part were Universiti Putra
Malaysia, Universiti Utara Malaysia, Universiti Sains Malaysia,
Universiti Teknologi Malaysia, Universiti Islam Antarabangsa,
Universiti Tenaga Nasional, Universiti Telekom Malaysia, Unitek
College, Olympia Business School, Help Institute, Informatics
College, Taylor's College and host UKM.
	   
