<HEADLINE>
Sangu mine to start soon, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Sangu mine to start soon, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The Sangu mine will start pumping 60 million cubic feet of gas
daily on completion of metre-connections within a couple of days.
	   Noor Uddin Khan said this on a supplementary question from ABM
Abul Kashem of Awami League.
	   The minister, who has lost his energy portfolio a few months
back, said the commissioning of Sangu gas field was scheduled for
April 22, but delayed for the metre-connection works.
	   Replying a started question from Shahidul Islam of BNP, Noor
Uddin said some 780 to 810 million cubic feet (mcft) gas is being
supplied daily from the country's 9 gas fields.
	   The breakdown: Titas 305 mcft, Habiganj 174 mcft, Narsingdi 20
mcft, Bakhrabad 93 mcft, Meghna 19 mcft, Salda River 17 mcft,
Sylhet 5 mcft, Kailashtila 93 mcft and Rashidpur 84 mcft.
	   The minister further told the House that 358 mcft or 44 per cent
of the total gas is consumed in power generation and 207 mcft or 26
per cent in fertiliser manufacturing.
	   The rest 245 mcft or 30 per cent is used in industrial,
commercial and domestic purposes.
	   On a separate question from Kazi Shah Mofazzal Hossain Koikobad,
Noor Uddin said the total reserve in Bakghrabad gas field is
estimated 867 billion cft.
	   Till last April, a total of 544.67 billion cft gas has been
extracted from the mine. Net pre-tax income from Bakhrabad was Tk
17.40 crore in 1996-97.
	   
</TEXT>
