	   TWENTY-FOUR teams from Selangor and Kuala Lumpur participated in
the annual Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia Netball Open Championship
held at the UKM campus in Bangi recently.
	   The one-day tournament was organised by the UKM Netball Club and
sponsored by Nestle.
	   In the final, Selangor Cemerlang beat Bank Simpanan Nasional
12-9 to the title.
	   The team received RM1,000 cash and the challenge trophy, Piala
Pusingan Suleiman Mohamed, donated by Deputy Information Minister
Datuk Suleiman Mohamed.
	   The trophy was presented by the special assistant to Suleiman,
Awaludin Johar, at the UKM Pavilion.
	   The BSN team received RM750 cash.
	   Third and fourth places went to Proton and Legend respectively
who received RM500 and RM250.
	   The best shooter award went to Juliana Jamaluddin of Selangor
Cemerlang, while Norizan Rejab of BSN was adjudged the best player.
	   Teams which took part in the tournament included Universiti
Putra Malaysia, Sapura, Denso, Texas Instruments and Institut
Teknologi Mara.
	   
