<HEADLINE>
DSE marks slight rise, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
DSE marks slight rise, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   On the gainers' dominance the trading at the Dhaka Stock
Exchange (DSE) registered slight rise after suffering loss for
three consecutive days.
	   The DSE All Share Price Index rose by 20.65 points, or 5.10 per
cant to 685.39 against previous day's close at 664.83 points.
	   Out of 127 issues traded on the day, 107 gained in value, 18
declined, and two remained unchanged while on the previous day 68
had declined, 55 gained and three remained unchanged in 126
transacted.
	   Market capitalisation on the day closed at Taka 61.64 billion
rising by over Taka 1.86 billion.
	   A total of 430,304 shares and debentures valued at Taka 3.7
crore changed hands up from previous day's 344,713 shares and
debentures worth Taka 3.19 crore.
	   Quasem Drycells topped the volume leaders trading 68,630 shares
while Chic Tex traded 56,500 shares, Rose Heaven Ball Pen 52,500
Beximco Pharma 46,300, and Shinepukur Holdings Ltd 22,200 shares.
	   The major gainers of the day were: Monno Jutex with a gain of
Taka 180 per share, Singer Bangladesh Limited with Taka 135.03,
Bangladesh Lamps Limited with Taka 122.91, and Apex Food with Taka
119.43 per share.
	   Major losers included: Pharmaco International falling by Taka 7
per share, Wata Chemical by Taka 7, Sreepur Textile by Taka 6.56,
and 7th ICB Mutual Fund by Taka 4 per share.
	   
</TEXT>
