<SLUG> BMA-PARADE-HELD sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BMA parade held, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
BMA parade held, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   President's Parade marking the Commissioning of the cadets of
the 38th BMA Long Course and the 17th BMA SSC special course was
held at the Bangladesh Military Academy (BMA) parade ground at
Bhatiary today.
	   Chief of Army Staff Lt General Muhammad Mustafizur Rahman
reviewed the smartly turned out parade and took salute at the
impressive march past.
	   Battalion Senior Under Officer Intekhab Haider Khan was adjudged
the best all-round cadet and awarded the coveted Sword of Honour,
according to an ISPR press release.
	   He also received the Chief of Army Staff's Gold Medal for the
best performance in the military subjects while Cadet Muhammad
Reazul Kabir the Osmani Gold Medal for the overall best academic
performance.
	   Meanwhile, the Hamid Company received the BMA Color for the
summer term on the basis of different inter-company competitions.
	   Addressing the newly commissioned officers, the Chief of Army
Staff said courage, discipline honesty, sincerity, loyalty and
above all patriotism were the main qualities of a military officer.
	   Hard training and regular exercise were the keys to success in
the life of a soldier, he said.
	   ``Boldness of personal character, professional excellence and
competence were essential for an able army officer in upholding the
image of the army, its honor and glorious tradition,'' Rahman said
asking them to reflect the professional experience in their life.
	   He expressed his optimism that the newly born officers would be
able to demonstrate their worth in their practical life through
sincerity, initiatives, hard labour and intelligence.
	   High civil and military officials, diplomats, parents and
relations of the cadets were also present on the occasion.
	   After the parade, the Chief of Army Staff visited the
commandant's office.
	   
</TEXT>
