	   Topics related to democracy and election will be included in
text books to raise the awareness level of the voters.
	   Chief Election Commissioner Mohammad Abu Hena disclosed this
while talking to a delegation of Bangladesh Manabadhikar Samanaya
Parishad (BMSP) at his office yesterday.
	   He said the topics will be included in the text books of
secondary, higher secondary and university levels, including old
age literacy, imam training and other programmes.
	   Abu Hena informed the delegation about the plan of the Election
Commission to prepare voter's identity card from August this year
and a month-long programme to correct the voter lists in July.
	   He said the ID card project containing accurate information of
the voters will be preserved in computers both at district and
central levels.
	   During the discussion, the BMSP delegation assured to cooperate
with the Election Commission in amending the voter lists and
distributing the voter's identity card.
	   Election Commissioner Abidur Rahman and Mushtaque Ahmed
Chowdhury, Secretary of the Election Commission Secretariat MM Reza
were also present, said an official handout.
	   
