<HEADLINE>
Roof top gardening will help alleviate poverty, says minister, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Roof top gardening will help alleviate poverty, says minister, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   State Minister for Youth, Sports and Culture Obaidul Kader had
said the genetic problems of the Bangalees are hindering the
development of sports and games in the country. He stressed for
improving the health of the players through nutrition and exercise.
	   Obaidul Kader was speaking at a press conference held at the
Directorate of Sports and Youths in the city yesterday afternoon.
	   The press conference was organised to mark the grape cultivation
on the roof top of the buildings in the city. He said roof top
gardening would help alleviate poverty in the country.
	   Explaining the importance of roof top gardening, Obaidul Kader
said that the youth of the country are the driving force of all
activities and they could play a vital role in developing the
country through self employment and income generating activities.
	   The government would disburse a good amount of money among the
youths, irrespective of their party affiliation, for
self-employment. In the meantime, the government has set up 240
additional thana offices to promote development work through the
youths. At present 470 offices had been functioning covering all
thana, district and divisional headquarters, he said.
	   Besides, 69 computer training centres would be set up by next
August in all district and divisional headquarters to encourage
self-employment among the youths.
	   
</TEXT>
