<HEADLINE>
FIFA approves replacements for South Africa and Cameroon
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Paris (AP) _ FIFA has approved two replacements for injured
South Africa and Cameroon players, an official said Thursday.
	   South Africa's goalkeeper Rene Arendse will be replaced by Paul
Evans of local club Supersport United, spokesman Keith Cooper said.
	   Arendse was injured in training Monday. LateTuesday, he had
damaged ligaments removed from his left knee.
	   Cameroon was allowed to replace Serge Kwetche with Abanda Jouan.
No details were immediately available.
</TEXT>
