<HEADLINE>
Next week's Madeira Island Open added as British Open qualifier
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ST. ANDREWS, Scotland (AP) _ Officials of the British Open
decided Thursday to include next week's Madeira Island Open as one
of its qualifying events.
	   The event was originally excluded because of a weakened field
due to play next week in the U.S. Open in San Francisco. But
officials ruled the event was a full-fledged European Tour
touranament and should be included.
	   The British Open will be played July 16-19 at Royal Birkdale in
northwest England.
