<HEADLINE>
Lightning, boat capsize claim 15 in Cox's Bazar, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Lightning, boat capsize claim 15 in Cox's Bazar, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Boat capsize and lightning claimed 12 lives in Cox's Bazar
district yesterday.
	   Some 15 persons were injured in the incidents. Of them four were
army personnel. Four persons are missing. The accidents occurred in
Cox's Bazar sadar, Ramu, Chakoria and Kutubdia thanas.
	   Cox's Bazar experienced the first rain of the season. A storm
blew at a speed of 80 kilometre per hour over the district.
	   Thunderbolt killed Hasna Begum (40) and an unidentified child in
Jhilongja union under Cox's Bazar sadar thana, Delwar Hossain
(32)in Kaiarbeel union and Syed Ahmed (50) of Uttar Dhurong union
in Kutubdia thana, Zaker Ahmed (35) and Rajlaxmi Das (31) of Kauar
Khop union in Ramu thana. Another unidentified child was killed in
lightning in Garjonia in Ramu thana. 10 persons were injured in
these incidents.
	   Nurul Amin (22) and Rahmat Ali (60) died after being struck by
lightning while they were working at a shrimp project at Rampura of
Chakoria thana. Bahadur Miah (23) and Kabir Ahmed (35) of Pekua
union were killed by lightning while they were working in a paddy
field.
	   Four army personnel were seriously injured in lightning at Ramu
army camp. They were admitted to Chittagong Combined Military
Hospital.
	   Nishu Barua (4) and Moktar Ahmed (50) drowned when an engine
boat carrying 12 passengers capsized in Matamuhuri river in
Chakoria thana. Local people recovered the bodies. Four passengers
were missing. Six passengers swam ashore.
	   
</TEXT>
