<SLUG> BC-Chechnya-Execution </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chechen man executed for killing mother
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A man convicted of murdering his mother was
executed by firing squad Thursday in the breakaway province of
Chechnya, a Russian news agency reported.
	   Magomed Vakhabov, 34, who was sentenced by an Islamic court,
became the fifth convicted criminal to face a firing squad in
Chechnya since last summer, Interfax said. Chechen television
planned to broadcast the execution.
	   Russia has established a moratorium on executions while it
considers a mandate by the Council of Europe to ban capital
punishment altogether. While Russia considers Chechnya to be part
of its national federation, Chechnya considers itself independent
and carries out most functions of an independent state.
	   (ml/ls) 	   
