	   The Finance Minister, SAMS Kibria, will present the budget for
1998-99 in Parliament at 3 pm today.
	   This will be the third national budget to be presented by
Kibria.
	   The first budget of the ruling Awami League government was
prepared by the Caretaker Government but it was adopted by the
Awami League government following assumption of power on June 23,
1996.
	   The Awami League government adjusted the budget with its
economic and political commitments before Kibria presented it to
the House at a delayed budget session.
	   Today's budget speech of the Finance Minister will be telecast
from Parliament.
	   
