<HEADLINE>
Toyota to recall 6 models with brake malfunctions: Report
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Toyota Motor Corp. announced Thursday it will
recall six compact car models because of a defective braking
system, a news report said.
	   A total of 118,355 Toyota vehicles manufactured between May 1997
and April 1998 will be recalled, Kyodo News service reported.
	   Toyota's Corolla II, Tercel and Starlet were among the models
that face the recall, Kyodo said.
	   The defect involves a faulty pedal sensor which misreads
pressure applied to the brakes, the report said.
	   Toyota and Transport Ministry officials were not immediately
available for comment.
