	   Two alleged 'phensidyl' traders were arrested from the city's
Dhanmondi area yesterday. Police recovered 1,100 bottles of
contraband 'phensidyl' syrup worth about Tk one lakh from their
possession.
	   A DB police squad, led by Assistant Commissioner Akram Hossain,
raided a house at 268, Elephant Road at about 8:30 am and arrested
Rahim Hawlader (26) and Selim (27) from the rooftop of the house.
But their leader Khaleque, who was wanted for half a dozen cases
with different DMP thanas, managed to leave the house.
	   Earlier on Tuesday night, another DB police squad recovered 432
cans of beer and several bottles of liquor worth about Tk 50,000
from a place adjacent to House No 41, Road No 21, Banani and
arrested Akbar Ali (35) in this connection.
	   Uttara police yesterday arrested one Ahsan Habib alias Titu from
a slum in Meradia Bhuiyapara under Sabujbagh thana and recovered 30
stolen ceiling fans from his possession.
	   On Tuesday night, Uttara police arrested Firoz Mian and Rafiqul
Islam Rafiq from Dakkhinkhan Naddapara area and recovered some
stolen automobile spare parts from their possession.
	   
