<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Bergkamp,0286 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Dutch striker close to fitness, could play Saturday
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With Sports-Soccer-Netherlands &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   VERSAILLES, France (AP) _ Belgium beware. Dutch striker Dennis
Bergkamp is approaching match fitness and could play in the
Netherlands' World Cup opener Saturday against its low countries
rival.
	   ``It is going very well at the moment,'' Bergkamp said Thursday
after the first Dutch training session on French soil. ``This is
one of the few times I have trained with the group. I do not feel
any pain any more.''
	   Bergkamp injured his hamstring six weeks ago playing for English
Premiership champion Arsenal. He has not played since and his
training has been limited.
	   But on Thursday he went through a full _ though not very
strenuous _ training session with the Dutch squad and emerged
smiling and unharmed.
	   The consolation for Belgium is that Bergkamp, who has 33
international goals to his name in 57 internationals, doesn't yet
feel fit enough to play 90 minutes.
	   ``I don't think I can play a full game yet. Maybe I could come
on in the second half. Belgium is probably too early for me.''
	   He said he was confident of playing against South Korea, the
Netherlands' second Group E opponent, on June 20 in Marseille, but
would not rush things for the Belgium confrontation.
	   ``It is a whole tournament, not just one game. I have to build
up my strength.''
	   Dutch coach Guus Hiddink also was pleased with Bergkamp's
progress but agreed that Saturday could be too soon for a return.
	   ``He is not complaining about the injury, but we have to build
him up (physically),'' the coach said.
	   (mc-sl)
</TEXT>
