<HEADLINE>
30 hurt in clashes between AL factions in Pabna, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
30 hurt in clashes between AL factions in Pabna, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   At least 30 people including two women were injured in two
separate clashes between rival factions of Awami League at south
Ragubpur area in the town on Thursday. Of the injured, seven were
rushed to the Sadar Hospital and clinics in critical condition.
They are Kanak (23), Panna (20), Johurul (25), Alim (20), Sattar
(22), Iqbal (35) and Joynab(25). Poilce and witnesses said , the
clash ensued at about 5.15 pm when both the groups equipped with
fire arms and other sharp weapons attacked each other following a
previous conflict over establishing supremacy in the area.
	   On the day of occurrence the rival groups of Awami League had a
meeting at Ragubpur area for settling the brawl that took place
between them earlier . At one stage of the meeting hot words were
exchanged between both the groups which resulted in the skirmishes.
During the hour-long clash both the groups exchanged at least 60
rounds of gunshots , blasted many cocktails and damaged two houses
. Police rushed to the scene and brought the situation under
control. Two persons were arrested in this connection.
	   In another clash between two factions of pro-Awami League
Chhatra League at Bhanguria Haji Jamal Uddin College left five
people injured including the VP of the college and general
secretary of Bhaunguri thana unit. The seriously injured Rezaul
Karim Bachchu, VP of the college, Awlad Hossain, GS of Bhaunguria
thana unit and two others were admitted to Bhaunguria thana health
complex.
	   
</TEXT>
