<HEADLINE>
Agitated consumers attack power offices in Natore, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Agitated consumers attack power offices in Natore, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Officers and employees of two Palli Bidyut samities under the
Rural Electrification Board (REB) and Natore Electric Supply Office
under the Power Development Board (PDB) have been passing their
days in sheer panic following the attacks of the agitated power
consumers due to erratic power supply. Three incidents of attacks
occurred during the first week of June in the district. An attack
was made on Natore Palli Bidyut Samity-2 (Bonpara) on June 3 last
leaving at least 20 employees including four security personnel
injured. A group of unruly power consumers equipped with lethal
weapons launched the attack.
	   The attackers damaged the safety gate of the samity, wireless
cell, Ansar Box, furniture and glass of the main building of the
samity. Four security men (Armed Ansars) were hurt during the
attack. The injured were admitted to Baraigram thana health
complex. Sources in the Natore Palli Biddyut Samity-2 said, the
daily demand of power for 42,000 consumers including North Bengal
Sugar Mills (Gopalpur), Sardah Police Academy, Rajshahi Cadet
College and about 1,000 power driven irrigation machines is 9
megawatts , but the supply is only 1 to 1.5 megawatt . That is why
the samity is forced to suspend power supply, sources said. Another
incident of attack was reported on June 5 on Natore Electric Supply
Office.
	   A group of unruly youths gherowed the office and damaged the
gloves, furniture's of the office building and threatened the
employees for abnormal loadsheding and frequent power disruption.
The supply situation was almost same in the office. The last
incident of attack was reported on Natore Palli Bidyut Samity-1
(Natore Sadar) on June 6. A group of villagers equiped with sharp
and lethal weapon tried to attack on it's Puthia sub-station office
and Natore main office on the same day protesting continuous power
disruption in it's locality.
	   Later police intercepted and brought the situation under
control. Law enforcing agency personnel have been deployed in three
key-point installations (three power office) to save the
establishments from possible attacks. Despite that, officers,
employees and workers of the three establishments in the district
have been working with life threat in the above circumstances.
	   
</TEXT>
