<HEADLINE>
Residential hotels in Jessore are safe havens for criminals, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Residential hotels in Jessore are safe havens for criminals, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Most of the residential hotels at Jessore town have become dens
of criminal activities and 'safe havens' for organised gang of
criminals. Although the members of the law enforcing agencies
sometimes raid these hotels , they hardly take action against the
persons involved in the clandestine activities . Only the gay girls
and the pimps are arrested and the 'god fathers' go scot free . As
a result, crimes of various descriptions including sexual orgies
have proliferated alarmingly, it is alleged. It may be mentioned
that the police earlier arrested pimps and call girls on several
occasions from Hotel Rina, Hotel Probal, Hotel Rupali etc, but the
managers and the staff or the owners of those residential hotels
remained at large. As a result, flesh trade at these residential
hotels has been going on.
	   Inmates of a residential hotel dare not bring call girls in
their rooms at their own initiatives. The hotel executives
generally supply these girls as desired by the boarders concerned
in exchange for earning extra money, well informed sources told.
The informed sources added that those boarders of the residential
hotels who crave to enjoy the prostitutes are possessors of black
money earned through smuggling , human trafficking or selling of
illegal arms. The executives of the residential hotels are in close
cooperation of these demoralised people . The owners of these
hotels in most cases are aware of the activities of their
executives.
	   But they keep mum for the interest of business. It is learnt
that two sub-inspectors of Kotwali thana Shahidul Islam Shaheen and
Emdadul Haque raided the residential hotel Rupali and Hotel Rina
respectively in the morning of May 26. SI Shaheen arrested three
gay girls and three clients from Hotel Rupali. Meanwhile, SI
Emdadul Haque arrested three pimps and two prostitutes from Hotel
Rina. The arrested pimps were identified as Billal of Shankarpur,
Selim of Loan Office Para and Zia-ul-Alam . Billal is a notorious
terrorist and extortionist. The pimps arrested from Hotel Rina are
Ajit Das, Swapan Saha and Ahmed Mia.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 THE INDEPENDENT all rights reserved as
distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
