	   CRUDE palm oil futures on the Kuala Lumpur Commodity Exchange
closed slightly higher on a weak ringgit but underlying
fundamentals remained fragile on lack of other fresh leads, dealers
said.
	   At the close, June gained RM15 to settle at RM2,345, July rose
RM14.00 to RM2,325, August added RM17.00 to RM2,305 and September
gained RM17.00 to RM2,290.
	   Turnover increased to 1,489 lots from 1,162 lots yesterday but
open interest decreased to 6,509 contracts from 6,769 contracts.
	   
