<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Romania struggles to plug gaps in its defense
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By VIOREL URMA &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   ALBI, France (AP) _ Ending two days of warmup games with local
teams Romanian coach Anghel Iordanescu still has a major problem to
plug gaps in the team's defense before Monday's opener against
Colombia.
	   ``I'm still dissatisfied with the weaknesses of our defense,''
Iordanescu said Thursday.
	   Already without Atletico Madrid's Daniel Prodan, who was left
out due to last month's knee surgery, Iordanescu told reporters
that another mainstay of the defense, Tibor Selymes of Anderlecht,
has a strained ankle and is unlikely to play in Lyon Monday.
	   Even worse for the Romanians, striker Adrian Ilie of Valencia,
nicknamed the ``Cobra'' for his habit of striking from nowhere,
missed the warmups on Wednesday and Thursday reportedly due to a
bruised leg. Team officials were silent about his chance of making
the team against Colombia.
	   So bad was the situation that in the Thursday game the Romanian
side had to borrow three players from the French squad of Albi to
be able to make the full team. Romania used its main lineup in the
first game Wednesday, while on Thursday it fielded its reserves.
	   Replacing Selymess was 26-year-old Liviu Ciubotariu of National
Bucharest of the Romanian first division.
	   ``Colombia is a technical team and the fate of the game is open
to both sides,'' Iordanescu said.
	   In the main game Wednesday, Romania gave an idea of what its
tactics against the Latin American team might look like, with
defender Dan Petrescu of Chelsea making devastating runs down the
left wing and midfielder Gheorghe Hagi dilligently supporting both
offense and defense.
	   In addition, 25-year-old Viorel Moldovan of Coventry City played
very offensively, much like a battering ram. Physically strong,
Moldovan came into his own as a goalscorer with Swiss club
Grasshoppers. He has not made an big impact in England, though.
	   After another day of practice Friday, the team will leave
Saturday for Lyon to prepare for the June 15 opener.
</TEXT>
