<SLUG> BC-Sports-Auto Racing-Mansell Injured </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Mansell injured in crash for British Touring Car Championship
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   DONINGTON, England (AP) _ Former Formula One world champion
Nigel Mansell suffered whiplash injuries in qualifying Thursday at
the Donington Park track for this weekend's British Touring Car
Championship.
	   Mansell, the '92 F1 champion, was injured when his Ford was hit
by a car driven by Mark Lemmer near the final chicane on the
circuit.
	   ``It could have been a lot worse,'' said Mansell, who said
Lemmer managed to steer clear of ramming him broadside. Mansell
suffered whiplash, a headache and a bruised jaw after the crash.
	   ``But he (Lemmer) was aware of what was going to happen and
picked a safer spot on the back of me, otherwise I might have been
seriously hurt.''
	   Mansell returned to testing during the afternoon session and was
expected to race Saturday.
	   (scw)	   
