AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Many accounts of misery have emerged from the Bosnian war. So it
is delightful to learn of an event which has left a Muslim family
in a village with two cars and the biggest house, rebuilt on its
war-ravaged ruins. It all began when the father gave two goldfish
from Austria to his teenage sons. Then war swept through the
village and the father died fighting.
	   After stealthily burying his body, his wife on a heaven-inspired
impulse, released the goldfish in the nearby lake believing they
would be more fortunate. And they were! When she returned to the
flattened village five years later, a glint of gold in the lake
made her look there intently. The lake swarmed with goldfish, some
fully gold in colour, others with black and white spots like the
original pair! Providentially, the lake had no predators.
	   Moreover, while the goldfish could not do with a heater at home,
here they were miraculously living and multiplying, even when the
lake froze hard enough for skaters to travel across. The woman
feeling blessed, fed the fish, and helped by her sons sold the fish
throughout the region. And all because of the legacy of the gift
from her husband to their children.
	   
</TEXT>
