<HEADLINE>
Government troops kill 10 Tamil rebels, government justifies news
</HEADLINE>
censorship &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: Sri Lankan military censors deleted the exact location of the
fighting from this report. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) _ The Sri Lankan defense ministry said
Thursday its troops killed 10 Tamil Tiger rebels in the northern
war zone, the current scene of one of the fiercest battles in the
country's 15-year-old civil war.
	   The ministry did not report deaths on the government side.
	   The rebels among Sri Lanka's Tamils demand a separate homeland,
accusing the Sinhalese majority of oppressing the Tamil minority.
The war began in earnest after 1983 ethnic riots in Colombo in
which hundreds of Tamil civilians were killed by Sinhalese
nationalists.
