<BODY>
<SLUG> OUR-SERVAVTS-A-POINTER sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Our servants: A pointer to social decadence ?, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Our servants: A pointer to social decadence ?, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
   Nilufar AzimASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   TO serve an individual or a group with obedience, sincerity and
faithfulness, is the duty of a servant. When a person serves the
government, he or she is a government servant and when serves a
private organization, is a non-government servant. A particular
person when engaged and employed in a domestic house with the
responsibilities of performing the household affairs, is called the
servant' in our society, male or female.Those days are almost gone
when the domestic servants were amiable, obedient and trustworthy.
We know lots of stories about the sacrifices and sincerity of a
servant. In the story of Khokababur Pratyabartan' (Return of the
master's son), written by Rabindranath Tagore, where we find how a
servant named Raicharan sacrifices his own child for the sake of
his master.
	   Because ``Raicharan was conscious of the fact that he himself
was at fault for the master's son being drowned in the river
Padma.'' He took the pain and agony himself instead of giving
sufferings to his master. Nowadays Raicharan's sacrifice instead of
being emulated, children are abducted and a heavy ransom is
demanded. Even in our childhood we have witnessed how we were taken
care of and our children were looked after by us. In the absence of
a master, the servant guided the whole family like a real
guardian.But what is wrong today? Servant means a person of
distrust, insincerity and hatred. At times they are real threat' to
us. Even when they are at fault, we are not in a position to take
them to task. I know a family where the lady of the house wanted
the accounts after the servant came back from the market. Proper
accounts were not given which excited the lady and she expressed
her anger.
	   Result was a vigorous outrage and finally it caused the lady's
death within a week and it was published in the paper also.Despite
everything we are very much dependent on the servants in all
household affairs as we can't perform our own duties ourselves.
There are families in Dhaka city where the servants are more in
number than the family members. When we go abroad and stay there,
we do our own job. Ofcourse the system and modern technology help
us there to take care of everything. Both the sexes work outside
and maintain the whole family in a very methodical way. Practically
our system here doesn't permit us to follow what we do
abroad.Domestic servants are also professional. They earn their
livelihood through this occupation. I feel we should take
initiative to form agencies, govt or non-govt, which should confirm
the employment of such professionals.
	   I know of such a private agency already existing and located in
Gulshan/ Baridhara where particulars of each and every individual
are recorded and verified by the police station of the area
concerned so that in case of any mishap, they could be traced
without having much trouble.But getting domestic professionals
through the agency mentioned is really expensive. Only the
foreigners and moneyed men of our society can afford this but for
the rest of the society it is a utopian scheme. So this is my
suggestion that there should be organisations like this all over
Bangladesh. I have seen similar organisations in India long time
back. This is one side of the coin, but what about the other?It is
happening very often that the servants are beaten, injured and
burnt to death by the members of the house which was really
unthinkable in our days. The maid servants are often molested and
violated by the male members of the family. Ours is a poor country,
they all come from a poverty-stricken family. Poverty doesn't mean
that they are to be treated as an object of tyranny.
	   Struggle for existence is not the loss of self-respect.
Sometimes it is also seen that the girl servants' become the victim
of sexual abuse and harassment when the female member has a hand in
it. This is a clear picture of abnormal behaviour of our vitiated
society.Relation between the master and the domestic help is
deteriorating very fast. Prevalence of devilish attitude is
endemic. One housewife was hacked to death in the city by the
paramour of her maid servant who was sacked by her and sent to the
village house few days back (The Independent, 30. 5.1998). They
were arrested and gave there confessional statement. So what is
happening today, is nothing but an act of mindless retaliation and
revenge. Eye for an eye, murder for a murder; for brutality there
are brutal activities. Now who is at fault - the master or the
servant?A social transformation is very much needed where social
structure should be reformed. Social values and moralities should
be given the highest' preference. ``The proper function of a
government is to make it easy for the people to do good and
difficult for them to do evil'' - Gladstone
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 THE INDEPENDENT all rights reserved as
distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
(PROFILE
(WS SL:OUR-SERVAVTS-A-POINTER sked; CT:w; 
(REG:ENGL;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
)
