<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, 2nd Ld,0315 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Lull in fighting as world weighs military and political action
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With BC-NATO-Kosovo, BC-Albania-NATO &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: RECASTS with Milosevic's party spokesman warning Yugoslavia
will not accept NATO actions on its territory without its consent. &QL; 
 &UR; By ISMET HAJDARI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia (AP) _ Yugoslavia warned Thursday it would
not tolerate unauthorized NATO actions on its territory, as the
alliance stepped up military pressure on President Slobodan
Milosevic to stop using force in the separatist province of Kosovo.
	   The warning from Ivica Dacic, spokesman for Milosevic's ruling
Socialists, came as NATO defense ministers decided to mount
simulated air raids and bombing runs over neighboring Albania and
Macedonia to deter Yugoslav forces from further military action in
Serbia's secessionist Kosovo province.
	   ``We are a sovereign country and without our consent no actions
of any international alliance can be carried out on our territory _
especially since there is no reason for it,'' Dacic said, according
to the independent FoNet news agency in Belgrade.
	   Dacic said Yugoslavia does not threaten regional stability or
peace, and denied allegations of ethnic cleansing against ethnic
Albanians, who make up 90 percent of Kosovo's population.
	   Yugoslav forces are defending ``territorial integrity ... from
terrorist actions,'' Dacic said.
	   In Kosovo, no fighting was reported by either side Thursday,
although skirmishes between heavily armed Serb forces and the
ethnic Albanian militants of the Kosovo Liberation Army have become
a daily occurrence.
	   More than 250 people have been killed since police began a
crackdown in March on militants in the province, where ethnic
Albanians have been ruled repressively since Serbia stripped Kosovo
of broad autonomy in 1989.
	    &UR; Tanjug, the, 6th graf 	   
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, 2nd Ld; CT:i; 
(REG:MEST;)
(REG:ENGL;)
(REG:AFRI;)
(REG:ASIA;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
