<HEADLINE>
Four people detained in Kyrgyzstan on suspicion of bombing
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Security forces detained four people in Kyrgyzstan
who they suspect were involved in two recent deadly explosions in
the city of Osh, a news agency reported Thursday.
	   A bomb on a bus and another in a house on May 30 and 31 killed
four people and wounded 11 in the Central Asian country, ITAR-Tass
said.
	   ITAR-Tass quoted an unidentified security officer as saying the
suspects were Wahhabis, members of a fundamentalist Islamic sect
blamed for recent violence in several parts of the former Soviet
Union.
