<BODY>
<SLUG> CARPETS-TO-COVER-ALL sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Carpets to cover all tastes, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Carpets to cover all tastes, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Hisham HarunASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   DID you know that most of the carpets used in our hotels, in
many of the main mosques and even in palaces are manufactured by a
Malaysian company?
	   Believe it. They are products of Carpets International Malaysia
(CIM), the country's largest carpet designer, manufacturer and
distributor.
	   Over the years, CIM, which was established in 1965, has grown
locally and internationally. In Malaysia, it controls about 30 per
cent of the market. The company has developed a wide range of
carpets to meet the needs of an impressive variety of clients.
	   The list includes palaces, luxury hotels, exclusive clubs and
commercial buildings, motor manufacturers, corporations and
government agencies.
	   CIM also boasts pioneering techniques and has its own in-house
design studio and a dye house.
	   These features offer customers unrivalled flexibility in the
commission and execution of designs and colour versatility.
	   In terms of weaving techniques, CIM offers a choice of five
different manufacturing processes - hand tuft, Axminster (woven),
machine tuft, needle punch and auto.
	   In the case of Axminster carpets which are the most popular type
for hotels, clubs, palaces and commercial buildings, CIM's only
competitors are foreign manufacturers.
	   Manufacturing facilities are housed in CIM's factory in Jalan
Kuchai Lama, Kuala Lumpur. The carpets are marketed under brand
names such as Fina Flor, Prestige, Shangril, Super Weave, Soft
Touch and Mosque Carpets.
	   Consultants advise clients on the most suitable carpets for
their needs.
	   With its experienced sales personnel and creative design team,
CIM is also able to work closely with architects, designers and
consultants to get the work done.
	   It is no surprise that CIM has an enviable reputation as
Malaysia's most creative carpet manufacturer. From plain to floral,
geometric to abstract, in a myriad of colours, CIM has some of the
loveliest rugs around.
	   What makes these carpets special is that they are not only
beautiful and tasteful but are made to last and last. What's more,
we can be proud that they are made-in-Malaysia and definitely much
cheaper than imported rugs.
	   This weekly column is devoted to made-in-Malaysia products,
concepts and services.
	   
</TEXT>
