<TEXT>
	   MUNICH, Germany (AP) _ German Transport Minister Matthias
Wissmann warned motorists Thursday to avoid the Brenner Pass, the
focal point of an blockade announced by environmentalists
protesting damage to the delicate Alpine ecosystem.
	   The two-day protest is expected to tie up traffic from southern
Germany into Italy over the long weekend for the Corpus Christi
holiday on Thursday.
	   The action is widely supported by Austrian politicians, although
Austrian authorities have said that they would not tolerate any
action that halts traffic through the pass connecting Italy and
Austria.
