<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,0904 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   The skies were partly cloudy on the north and east coasts of
Puerto Rico where there were scattered showers moving onshore.
Elsewhere, including the Virgin Islands, the skies were mostly
clear and free of any precipitation. The wind was from the
northeast at near 10 mph or calm. The temperatures ranged from 70
to 80 degrees.
	   An upper-level low pressure trough passed to the south of Puerto
Rico and the Virgin Islands Wednesday morning. This put the
northern Caribbean in a drier and more stable air mass. Moisture is
limited to the very lowest layers of the atmosphere. A short wave
low pressure trough will move rapidly southward from the coasts of
New Jersey and Delaware today and will reach Puerto Rico on Friday.
This short wave will cause an increase in showers and afternoon
thunderstorms on Friday.
	   The small craft advisory for the Caribbean outer waters was
discontinued. Small boat operators however should use caution today
especially in the off shore waters due to northeast to east winds
of 15 to 20 knots and seas around five feet. The winds and seas are
expected to decline significantly on Friday.
 &UR; San Juan and north sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly cloudy. A 40 percent chance of showers mostly
in the morning. Breezy afternoon. High 85 to 90. Wind northeast 15
to 20 mph.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy east with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Fair west. Low 75 to 80. Wind light east.
	   Friday ... Increasing clouds with a 40 percent chance of
showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High around 90. Wind east around
10 mph.
 &UR; East sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Variable cloudiness this morning. Becoming mostly
sunny and breezy afternoon. A 40 percent chance of morning showers.
High from 85 to 90. Wind northeast 10 to 20 mph.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80. Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   Friday ... Increasing clouds with a 40 percent chance of
showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east around 10
mph.
 &UR; Ponce and south sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Mostly sunny. A slight chance of showers. Possible
afternoon thunderstorm inland. High around 90. Wind southeast 10 to
15 mph. Chance of rain is less than 20 percent.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy east with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Fair west. Low 70 to near 80. Wind light northeast.
	   Friday ... Increasing clouds with a 30 percent chance of
showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High around 90. Wind southeast 10
to 15 mph.  &QR; 
 &UR; Mayaguez and west sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly cloudy morning. Variable cloudiness and breezy
afternoon. A 40 percent chance of showers and afternoon
thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east 15 to 20 mph except for an
afternoon sea breeze less than 10 mph along the west coast.
	   Tonight ... Generally fair. Low 65 to 75. Wind light southeast.
	   Friday ... Mostly sunny morning. Increasing cloudiness afternoon
with a 40 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to
90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph except for a weak west wind along the
west coast in the afternoon.
 &UR; Interior sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly cloudy morning. Variable cloudiness afternoon
with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated thunderstorms. Breezy
afternoon higher elevations. High from 75 to 80 mountains to 85 to
90 lower elevations. Wind east 10 to 20 mph.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy east with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Fair west. Low 65 to 70 mountains to 70 to 75 low valleys.
Wind southeast less than 10 mph.
	   Friday ... Partly cloudy morning. Increasing cloudiness
afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated
thunderstorms. High from 75 to 80 mountains to 85 to 90 lower
elevations. Wind east to southeast around 10 mph.
 &UR; St. Thomas, St. John and St. Croix
	   Today ... Partly cloudy and locally breezy. A 20 percent chance
of showers mostly this morning. High around 90. Wind northeast 15
to 20 mph.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Low around 80. Wind east near 10 mph.
	   Friday ... Variable cloudiness with a 40 percent chance of
showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High around 90. Wind east 10 mph.
 &UR; Puerto Rico and u.S. Virgin Islands waters
	   Synopsis ... High pressure near Bermuda dominates the weather
over the northern Caribbean and Bahamas. A weak tropical wave in
the eastern Caribbean will pass south of Puerto Rico tonight and
Friday.
 &UR; Atlantic waters
	   Small craft exercise caution.
	   This afternoon ... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 4 to 6 ft. Widely
scattered showers.
	   Tonight ... Wind east 10 to 15 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft. Widely
scattered showers.
	   Friday ... Wind east 10 kt. Seas 2 to 3 ft. Scattered showers.
 &UR; Caribbean waters
	   Small craft operators should exercise caution.
	   This afternoon ... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Near shore waters seas
3 to 4 ft. Off shore waters seas 4 to 6 ft. Scattered showers.
Isolated thunderstorms southwest waters.
	   Tonight ... Wind east 15 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft. Scattered showers.
Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Friday ... Wind east 10 kt. Seas 3 ft. Scattered showers.
