<HEADLINE>
Hashish to be destroyed in Turkmenistan
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Three tons of hashish seized by security forces in
Turkmenistan will be destroyed at a military site 70 kilometers (45
miles) outside the capital, a news agency reported Thursday.
	   The hashish, worth an estimated dlrs 6 million, originated in
Afghanistan, Interfax said. The drugs were intended for sale in
Turkmenistan, even though the Central Asian country has become a
key transit point for drugs destined for Russia and Europe.
	   Security forces said they seized more than 40 tons of drugs last
year, more than in all the other former Soviet republics in Central
Asia combined.
	   (ls) 	   
