<SLUG> BC-Sri Lanka-McDonald's,0183 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
McDonald's fast food chain to open in Sri Lanka
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By SHRI NAVARATNAM &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) _ U.S burger giant McDonald's will open
its first restaurants in Sri Lanka in September, an official said
Thursday.
	   Rusi Pestonjee, director of Abans Restaurant Systems Ltd, which
last year signed a 20-year franchise to manage and run McDonalds'
in Sri Lanka, said dlrs 3 million was invested in the first
restaurant, in the capital city of Colombo.
	   A second restaurant is planned, he said, adding that food will
be made extra spicy to suit the Sri Lankan palate.
	   McDonald's has begun training farmers who will supply
restaurants, although initially some ingredients will be imported.
	   The franchise will work with a mostly local staff of 70, half of
whom will be sent to the United States in July for training,
Pestonjee said.
	   Two other U.S. fast food chains, Kentucky Fried Chicken and
Pizza Hut, opened branches in Sri Lanka three years ago.
	   McDonald's has nearly 20,000 restaurants in more than 95
countries.
</TEXT>
