<HEADLINE>
Admiral Lopez of NATO's Southern Command to Retire
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ Admiral T. Joseph Lopez, commander of NATO's
Southern European command and U.S. Naval Forces Europe, is retiring
from the U.S. Navy.
	   Lopez is retiring to pursue a civilian career, said NATO
spokesman Major Nicolaos Halvatzis.
	   His retirement ends a 38-year naval career in which the West
Virginia native rose from enlisted sailor to one of the four
top-ranking officers in NATO's command structure.
	   A Vietnam veteran, Lopez took over NATO's southern European
command, based in Naples, Italy, and Naval Forces Europe a little
less than two years ago. He also headed the NATO-led peacekeeping
force in Bosnia from July 1996 until November 1996.
	   A tenure of two to three years as southern commander is
considered normal, Halvatzis said.
	   He said no date has been set for Lopez' retirement yet.
	   (cph) 	   
