</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> MEXICO-LOSES-ITS-DOCTOR sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MEXICO LOSES ITS LEADING DOCTOR, THE NEWS
</HEADLINE>
Mexico Loses Its Leading Doctor, The News &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   THE NEWS
   MEXICO
   ENGLISH
LATIN AMERICA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E.,

<TEXT>
2nd Floor WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax:
202-546-4194 COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE
OF FDCH, INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS
CONTAINED HEREIN MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO
WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   One of Mexico's greatest doctors of medicine, Dr. Salvador
Zubiran died of a heart attack Wednesday morning at his home. He
was 99.
	   The central auditorium of the National Institute For Nutrition,
founded by Zubiran in the 1940s, was adorned with white flowers in
honor of its founder. Considered one of Mexico's most famous
physicians, Zubiran headed the institute for 30 years. He also
founded the Mexican School of Medicine and was rector of the
National Autonomous University of Mexico (UNAM).
	   Zubiran's coffin was placed at the center of the Institute's
atrium where specialists and physicians from all medical fields
were able to lay tributes to Zubiran.
	   In recognition of his work President Ernesto Zedillo (back from
the U.N. summit on drugs) and his wife, Nilda Patricia Velasco de
Zedillo initiated the funeral ceremony which was later elaborated
by UNAM Rector Francisco Barnes de Castro and Social Security
Institute General Director Genaro Borrego.
	   Zubiran leaves his wife, Maria Luisa Lopez Collada, who remained
predominately emotive and tearful throughout the ceremony but later
gave thanks for the homage paid to her husband. Zubiran's doctor
consoled his family by assuring them he died painlessly and above
all peacefully.
	   Zubiran will be cremated Thursday and his ashes will be placed
in a crypt at the ancient Santa Cruz Church in Mexico City's
Colonia Pedregal.
	   Zubiran is survived by his wife and five children: Salvador,
Martha, Yoland, Gloria and Graciela.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 THE NEWS all rights reserved as distributed by
WorldSources, Inc. 	   
