<SLUG> BC-Britain-Let Them Wear Pants </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
After 145 years, girls at English private school to wear pants
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CHELTENHAM, England (AP) _ After 145 years of making girls wear
skirts to class, one of England's top private schools has decided
to let them wear pants.
	   Sixth-formers at Cheltenham Ladies' College _ the equivalent of
high school seniors _ will be allowed to swap their school uniform
skirts for a pair of regulation navy trousers, starting in
September.
	   The move came after college chiefs asked parents and students
their views on plans to redesign the school uniform, school
spokesman Kim Hill said Thursday.
	   ``The uniform had not changed a great deal since the war and I
think that was just because it never occurred to anybody before,''
she said. ``Tradition has a certain amount to do with it, but
everyone seems happy that the option to wear trousers should be
given to the girls.''
	   Students in the lower grades, however, still must wear their
traditional skirts and blouses.
	   (kg)
