<HEADLINE>
Lonrho to sell Princess Hotels to Canadian Pacific
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The shrinking conglomerate Lonrho PLC said
Thursday it agreed to sell its Princess Hotels subsidiary to
Canadian Pacific Ltd. for dlrs 540 million as part of its strategy
to focus on mining.
	   Canadian Pacific Hotels and Resorts Inc., a unit of the Canadian
Pacific rail and shipping group, will assume dlrs 71 million in
debt as part of the deal. Lonrho will use dlrs 56 million of its
proceeds to pay back other parts of the hotel chain's debts.
	   Lonrho, a trading company with extensive interests in Africa,
spun off its non-mining assets in Africa last month into Lonrho
Africa, a separate company listed on the London Stock Exchange.
	   The deal to sell the Princess Hotels ``substantially completes
the process of focusing Lonrho on its high-quality mining
operations,'' said the company's chairman, Sir John Craven.
	   (db-acw)
