<BODY>
<SLUG> Gucci earnings down amid takeover talk </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   MILAN, Italy (AP) _ Italy's chic leathergoods firm, Gucci, said
Thursday its net income in the first quarter of 1998 fell to dlrs
43.1 million from dlrs 48 million in the same period last year.
	   It said revenues fell to dlrs 250.7 million from dlrs 254.3
million.
	   The results come amid rumors that the Prada fashion house, which
announced last weekend it had acquired a 5 percent stake in Gucci,
might be planning a takeover.
	   In an interview with newspaper Il Messagero this week, Gucci
chief executive officer Domenico De Sole suggested that Prada
doesn't have the money for a takeover. Prada has yet to say what
its plans are.
	   Gucci said sales in the United States in the first quarter
inched down to dlrs 74.1 million from dlrs 75.6 million, while
sales in Europe rose to dlrs 68.2 million from dlrs 55.2 million.
	   Sales in Asia fell to dlrs 99.6 million from dlrs 118.8 million
while sales in the rest of the world rose to dlrs 8.8 million from
dlrs 4.7 million.
	   (dj/cph)
</TEXT>
