	   BARISAN Nasional backbencher Hilmi Rashid (BN-Bertam) yesterday
criticised the local authority for approving the establishment of
an entertainment outlet between two secondary schools in Kepala
Batas.
	   Hilmi said he learnt that the authority had allowed the outlet a
permit to operate between Sekolah Menengah Datuk Abdul Kader and
Sekolah Menengah Datuk Ahmad Badawi.
	   ``I will go there (entertainment outlet) and find out which
officer approved and signed the licence.
	   ``The office should be more sensitive, especially when approving
such entertainment outlets in areas where schools are located,'' he
said when debating the Bill on Entertainment and Places of
Entertainment Enactment 1997.
	   Jasmin Mohamed (BN-Sungai Dua) said the authorities should stop
approving permits for such outlets in small towns and rural
districts.
	   ``I am sure tourists will not patronise outlets in such areas so
why allow them a permit in the first place?'' he said.
	   
