<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-France-Indecent Scots </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bold Scottish supporters brighten up Paris
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) - Scottish supporters in town for the World Cup have
added a new dimension to French cultural life, showing incredulous
Parisians that Scotsmen really are naked under their kilts.
	   Members of the Tartan Army, in Paris to support their soccer
team, are not only drinking, singing and playing the bagpipe, but
many of them are also lifting their skirts and risk being charged
with indecent exposure.
	   ``We have been notified by police reports that some Scottish
supporters were, on Tuesday night, lifting their kilts and
revealing themselves naked,'' said the Paris prosecutors' office
Thursday. ``But since no complaints have been made nor fines given,
we are not planning on pursuing the matter.''
	   Therese, a Parisian legal secretary, who witnessed one of the
numerous incidents during the World Cup kick-off parade Tuesday,
said the revealing moment happened accidentally.
	   ``It wasn't vulgar or crude,'' she said, describing the moment
when the wind caught the Scotsmens' kilts while they were standing
above a subway air vent on the Champs Elysees.
	   The Scotsmen were taken by surprise, much to the amusement of
by-standers.
	   ``It all happened in a great friendly spirit,'' Therese added,
giggling. She did not want her last name used.
	   Some people, such as U.S. tourist Lori Anglin, were just pleased
to see that the legend was true.
	   Having spotted yet another of the Tartan Army's revealing
exercises on a bridge near the Eiffel Tower, Anglin said: ``It's
true what they've always said about Scots - they have nothing under
their kilt. Even on a blustery day they're truly the
brave-hearted.''
	   (ckp-dgs)	   
</TEXT>
