<HEADLINE>
Dollar up, gold down
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with late rates &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar gained against other key
currencies in European trading Thursday. Gold fell.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Wednesday:
	   _1.8040 German marks, up from 1.7982
	   _141.73 Japanese yen, up from 141.50
	   _1.4924 Swiss francs, up from 1.4883
	   _6.0485 French francs, up from 6.0300
	   _2.0325 Dutch guilders, up from 2.0266
	   _1,775.70 Italian lire, up from 1,772.50
	   _1.4645 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4673
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6299, up from dlrs
1.6282.
	   Gold closed in London at dlrs 289.60 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 293.10 Wednesday.
	   In Zurich the bid price was dlrs 289.90, down from dlrs 293.60.
	   Gold rose dlrs 1.70 in Hong Kong at dlrs 293.95 bid.
	   Silver closed in London at dlrs 5.23 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 5.37.
	   (rb)
