<SLUG> BC-Ethiopia-Bombing </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Eritreans bomb northeastern Ethiopian town
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos planned &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ADIGRAT, Ethiopia (AP) _ Eritrean aircraft on Thursday dropped
eight bombs on this northeastern Ethiopian border town, killing at
least one person, injuring three and setting grain warehouses
ablaze, witnesses said.
	   The first two bombs were dropped from a helicopter at 5:20 p.m.
(1420gmt) near an army base, but they apparently failed to hit
anything.
	   Jet fighters dropped four on the mountains surrounding the town,
and two on the combined industrial-residential area where the
warehouses are located in the town of some 40,000 inhabitants.
	   The attack occcured on the same day both Ethiopia and Eritrea
said fighting had broken out on the border near Eritrea's Red Sea
port of Assab.
	   Since May 6, the two countries in the Horn of Africa have been
fighting for control of territory along at least four different
points on their common border.
	   Adigrat is 125 kilometers (78 miles) south of the Eritrean
capital, Asmara and about 25 kilometers (15 miles) south of the
border.
	   (sa/sl)	   
</TEXT>
