<SLUG> BC-Norway-Perky Prisoner,0137 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Prisoner on jogging tour leaves his guards in the dust
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   OSLO, Norway (AP) _ A Norwegian prisoner proved the value of
physical fitness when he ran away from his four prison guards
during a jog and escaped.
	   When the small entourage reached a recreation area outside the
prison in the northern town of Bodoe, the prisoner picked up the
pace, pulled ahead of his jailors and escaped, the Norwegian news
agency NTB reported on Thursday. The agency did not say when he
escaped.
	   The prisoner, identified only as a man in his late 20s, had been
jailed for petty crimes. He had been granted special privileges,
including excursions outside the prison, the report said.
	   The escapee can expect to have his privileges revoked, assuming,
of course, that police catch up to him. 	   
