Hoards of cameras deter duchess from seeing Istanbul sights
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photo, IST101 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ISTANBUL, Turkey (AP) _ Weary of an army of cameras pestering
her in the sweltering heat, Fergie cut short her sightseeing tour
of Istanbul on Thursday.
	   Sarah Ferguson, the duchess of York, admired the 17th-century
Blue Mosque, but gave the Covered Bazaar and two famous Ottoman
palaces a miss.
	   In the morning, she visited a children's hospital, promising to
help raise drs 1 million. The duchess, who is the ex-wife of
Britain's Prince Andrew, was to attend a fundraiser for the
hospital later in the day.
	   Fergie was in Istanbul as the guest of the owner of Star TV, Cem
Uzan. Uzan's aides tried to persuade cameramen and photographers to
back off. When that failed, they said the duchess was cutting short
her sightseeing because of their constant pushing and shoving.
