	   RELA has been urged to establish more units in new housing
estates to help improve security for residents.
	   Balakong State Assemblyman Hoh Hee Lee said the organisation
could complement efforts by police which was facing a shortage of
staff.
	   He said Rela members could help curb crime and other social
problems by getting more local residents to join the organisation.
	   He was speaking to 150 Rela members, include 10 women, who
participated in the annual Hulu Langat District Rela shooting
competition at the Kajang Shooting Club practice ground in Sungai
Jeluh, Kajang recently.
	   Hoh said the housing estates in his constituency like Taming
Jaya, Sungai Ramal Long House needed Rela units to help reduce
crime.
	   On efforts to improve the Rela image, he said it should organise
more publicity campaigns on its role in society.
	   He praised the district Rela for organising the function and
encouraging an interest in shooting.
	   ``This shooting ground is among the few public shooting centres
owned by a shooting club, therefore more people in the district can
come and learn about shooting.''
	   Hoh also agreed to help the district Rela equip the new Kajang
Rela activity centre in Sungai Chua which is still under
construction.
	   District Rela officer Suprat Karjani, in his welcome speech,
said the 2,000 Rela members in the district also organised
community projects.
	   
