<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Italy-Chile-Halftime,0277 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Italy-Chile tied 1-1 at halftime
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BORDEAUX, France (AP) _ Marcelo Salas tied the game three
minutes into first half injury time as Chile hit back to hold Italy
1-1 at half time of their World Cup game Thursday.
	   Christian Vieri fired the Italians ahead after 10 minutes off a
sideways pass by Roberto Baggio and the leveller came from a corner
in the 48th minute.
	   Fabien Estay swung in the flag kick, Ivan Zamorano powered in a
header, Pedro Reyes touched the ball on and Salas, who joins
Italy's Lazio next season, turned to fire the ball home.
	   Italy, playing in all-white, took the lead in the 10th minute
with a stunning counter-attack after Zamorano, who ironically plays
for Inter Milan, lost possession deep in the Italian half.
	   Vieri and Baggio were well advanced with only two Chilean
defenders between them and the goal and the 1994 World Cup star
collected a long through ball from Paolo Maldini.
	   Instead of heading for goal, Baggio unselfishly slipped the ball
sideways to the better positioned Vieri who slid it home from 15
yards (meters) with his left foot.
	   Lineups:
	   Italy _ Gianluca Pagliuca; Alessandro Nesta, Paolo Maldini,
Fabio Cannavaro, Alessandro Costacurta, Dino Baggio, Angelo Di
Livio, Demetrio Albertini, Roberto Di Matteo, Christian Vieri,
Roberto Baggio.
	   Chile _ Nelson Tapia; Ronald Fuentes, Pedro Reyes, Javier
Margas, Moises Villarroel, Francisco Rojas, Nelson Parraguez,
Clarence Acuna, Fabian Estay, Ivan Zamorano, Marcelo Salas.
	   Referee: Lucian Bouchardeau, Nigeria.
	   (pv-rjm)	   
</TEXT>
