<SLUG> ZECON-BANKS sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Zecon banks on its customers to do well, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Zecon banks on its customers to do well, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   ZECON Engineering Berhad is expected to cushion the impact of
the present economic difficulties by depending on its ``wide base
and steady stream of customers''.
	   Executive chairman Zainal Abidin Ahmad said: ``The fact that we
are specialists and market leaders in the sub-sectors of foundation
and piling works, mechanical and electrical engineering as well as
in geo-technical works ensure that we have a wide base and steady
stream of customers.''
	   He added that it also helped that during the good years, Zecon
had restrained itself from diversifying aggressively.
	   ``We do not have the difficult task of down-sizing or
retrenching like other companies,'' he said after Zecon's annual
meeting in Kuching, Sarawak.
	   On the company's outlook for the current year, Zainal said Zecon
expected a slight dip in its profits in view of the current
economic situation but expressed optimism that the ``picture will
be much brighter by 1999''.
	   Zainal said the company had always been a prudent player and
this had been proven wise in this difficult times.
	   ``We have always kept a good eye on productivity and operational
efficiency and the figures (for 1997) show that we are on the right
track.''
	   Zecon managed to record positive growth for the year ended Dec
31, 1997 even though group turnover dipped slightly from RM103.49
million in 1996 to RM100.24 million last year.
	   Zecon, which is listed on the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange's
second board, recorded a group pre-tax profit of RM9.95 million
last year which was RM1.70 million or 16.8 per cent better than the
pre-tax profit recorded in 1996.
	   In future, Zecon plans to make inroads into property
development.
	   
</TEXT>
