<SLUG> BC-Belarus-Ambassadors </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ambassadors take protest letter to Belarusian foreign ministers
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MINSK, Belarus (AP) _ Diplomats from 14 countries facing
eviction from their homes delivered a formal protest letter
Thursday to the Belarusian Foreign Ministry.
	   Belarus has told residents of a diplomatic compound they must
vacate their homes by June 17 so that urgent repairs can be made to
the sewage and water systems.
	   The ambassadors say that under international law, their
residences are considered sovereign territory and governments have
no right to enter without permission or insist that diplomats
leave.
	   Diplomats from 22 countries live in the compound in the pine
forests on the outskirts of Minsk. Ambassadors from Bulgaria and
some former Soviet republics have left, but the United States and
others want to stay during the repairs.
	   (ls) 	   
