	   HALIM Securities Sdn Bhd's application to strike off a
winding-up petition by Multi Purpose Bank Bhd has been adjourned to
June 16.
	   In the petition filed on March 19, Multi Purpose is seeking to
wind up Halim Securities over its failure to pay loan facilities
amounting to RM15.9 million.
	   Halim Securities, which is already under trading restrictions,
was placed under the direct supervision of the Kuala Lumpur Stock
Exchange from March 23 to prevent payment defaults and other
trading breaches by the stockbroker.
	   Multi Purpose also applied to strike off the validation order
obtained by Halim to pay its normal operating expenses including
salaries and Employees Provident Fund payments on April 29 from the
High Court.
	   Multi Purpose's application on this subject has been scheduled
to be heard today.
	   Following this, Arab-Malaysian Merchant Bank sought an order
from the High Court on June 5 to validate the transfer of 40
million shares of Halim securities owned by Uniphoenix Corporation
to its nominee.
	   The Halim shares were pledged by Uniphoenix to Arab-Malaysian as
security for a syndicate loan of RM50 million. This matter is
scheduled to be heard on July 9.
	   Apart from that, Uniphoenix Corporation Bhd's application to
strike off the winding up petition by Multi Purpose Bank has been
postponed to June 22.
	   
</TEXT>
