<SLUG> BC-Canada-Sagging Dollar,0117 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Canadian dollar sets new all-time trading low
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TORONTO (AP) _ The Canadian dollar fell Thursday to an all-time
trading low of 60.03 U.S. cents.
	   The previous low, set Jan. 29, was 68.10 cents.
	   The Canadian currency has been weak for months because of the
negative impact of the Asian financial crisis on some Canadian
commodity exports. Canada's central bank has resisted raising
interest rates to protect the currency.
	   The weak dollar has been an annoyance for Canadians traveling to
the United States, but it has attracted U.S. bargain-hunters to
Canada and has helped some Canadian firms by making their exports
more affordable for U.S. buyers.
</TEXT>
