	   WITH the deliberate intention of breaking away from the norm, a
group of former students of Convent Bukit Nenas decided to have
their get-together at the Lifestyle Karaoke Lounge of Holiday Villa
Subang Jaya recently.
	   The Class of '86 students let their hair down and had a whale of
a time at the function.
	   Organising committee chairman Syirin Zarina said it was the
second meeting since the last one held two years ago.
	   ``We have about 120 ex-students from the 1986 batch but we only
managed to get in touch with about 90.
	   ``We felt this number was good enough to call for a party,''
Syirin said.
	   She said the main aim of the get-together was to keep in touch
with each other and to build a business network.
	   ``Our Old Girls are holding high posts in the various business
fraternity and the meeting will offer an excellent opportunity to
meet and discuss possible avenues for business expansion,'' Syirin
said.
	   
