<BODY>
<SLUG> INFO-STORAGE-MARKET sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SSM going for growth in info storage market, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
SSM going for growth in info storage market, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Rosabel ThomasASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SAPURA Systems (M) Sdn Bhd (SSM), a member of the Sapura Group,
believes it can obtain more revenue contribution from the
information storage market for the coming year. SSM, which is the
local distributor of ATL's digital linear tape (DLT) libraries,
also expects to increase its market share by 100 per cent.
	   SSM's marketing manager Wan Ahmad Kamal said efforts would be
made to raise awareness among corporate users on the importance of
proper information storage within their organisations.
	   The company plans to conduct aggressive indirect marketing
activities through its 35 channel partners nationwide.
	   ``On top of that, we have also directly planned to market these
products by conducting roadshows and other joint events with ATL,''
Wan Ahmad said.
	   SSM, he added, will also leverage on its regional and
local-based advertisements in an effort to increase its revenue in
the information storage market.
	   Wan Ahmad was speaking to reporters at a Press conference held
in Kuala Lumpur last week in conjunction with the launch of ATL's
latest range of information storage products. The products are the
P1000, P3000, PowerStor L500 libraries and the PL50 Library Hub,
which are developed using the Prism architecture.
	   At the same event, ATL's regional general manager for
Asia-Pacific Graham Timm said Prism is a new library architecture
that seeks to shatter the constraints of the conventional approach
to storage performance, and thus redefines the library system
design. By incorporating a cost- effective, high-performance
peripheral component interconnect (PCI) expansion bus into
automated tape systems, the Prism architecture has reached a
pinnacle in open systems design.
	   ``By harnessing the power of high-speed PCI adapter cards, the
Prism libraries can be upgraded by adding library building blocks.
The upgrade enables network and fibre connectivity and provides
capability to embed servers and functionality such as tape
mirroring and auto tape copy,'' Timm said.
	   He added that libraries which utilise the Prism technology are
compatible with all Unix and Windows NT environments.
	   ``Its support of open system storage management provides a high
degree of flexibility and compatibility to the end users in
ensuring that their investments are protected.''
	   The P1000 provides the capability of supporting up to four DLT
4000 or DLT-7000 drives and 30 DLT cartridges for 72 gigabytes (GB)
per hour performance. It also allows cost-effective expansion by
adding only drives and cartridge slots, thus eliminating the need
to buy a new library.
	   Targeted at storage-intensive applications, the P3000 features
up to 16 DLT drives and 332 cartridges for 288GB per hour
performance. The high availability design features hot-swap DLT
drives, power supplies, fans and AC sources.
	   The PowerStor L500 meanwhile is targeted at small to
medium-sized industries (SMIs). It supports up to three DLT drives
and 14 DLT cartridges and delivers 54GB per hour back-up
performance.
	   The PL50 Library Hub presents a virtual library to three
heterogeneous back-up servers by allowing a user to assign a
cartridge slot and drive partitions. It is equipped with four small
computer systems interface (SCSI) ports, a monitor and advanced
library hub software, Timm said.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
(PROFILE
(WS SL:INFO-STORAGE-MARKET sked; CT:w; 
