<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-France-World Cup-Sorry Scot </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
French court convicts rowdy Scottish soccer fan
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ A French court Thursday convicted a Scottish soccer
fan accused of throwing a beer cans at a French policeman and
sentenced him to a two-month suspended sentence.
	   Christopher Kyles, 23, of Aberdeen, Scotland, apologized to the
court. Speaking through a translator, he admitted being drunk and
remembered none of his actions.
	   Kyles was accused of throwing a beer can at French police on the
Champs Elysees during festivities Tuesday night in Paris that
marked the opening of the World Cup.
	   Late-night clashes between drunken soccer fans, Parisian youths
and riot police left 34 policemen injured during the soccer party.
	   Following his arrest, police seized Kyles' ticket and put him in
jail, preventing Kyles from attending the Brazil-Scotland match on
Wednesday, which his country lost 2-1.
	   Scots have startled many Parisians with their hard drinking and
tendency to lift their kilts, often revealing naked bottoms.
	   (parf-dgs) 	   
</TEXT>
