<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-DFS Classic </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Graf wins second match of comeback
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BIRMINGHAM, England (AP) _ Steffi Graf took just one hour to
beat Kristie Boogert in straight sets Thursday and advance to the
quarterfinals of the DFS Classic.
	   In her second match in four months, the former world No. 1
player dominated the Dutch qualifier 6-2, 6-4 on another
rain-affected day at Edgbaston.
	   The top-seeded Graf, wearing warmup pants on a cold and overcast
day, looked sharper than the previous day when she needed three
sets to beat Australia's Rennae Stubbs.
	   Graf took the first set in 28 minutes with breaks in the third
and seventh games and raced to a 3-0 lead in the second set.
Boogert won three straight games to even the set at 3-3 before Graf
regained command.
	   Graf is playing in only her third tournament since undergoing
knee surgery a year ago. She is preparing for Wimbledon, a
tournament she has won seven times.
	   Second-seeded Irina Spirlea had to wait four days to play her
first match of the tournament but took just 63 minutes to beat
Canada's Maureen Drake 6-4, 6-2 and advance to the third round.
</TEXT>
