<SLUG> BC-Belarus-Egypt </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
President of Belarus to visit Egypt
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MINSK, Belarus (AP) _ President Alexander Lukashenko of Belarus
will visit Egypt on Monday and Tuesday, his office said.
	   Lukashenko is scheduled to meet with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak and other senior officials.
	   ``Belarus sees cooperation with Egypt as especially important
because Egypt is a country which is energetically restructuring and
developing its economy,'' deputy prime minister Leonid Kozik said
Thursday.
	   Belarus has made fewer economic reforms than probably any other
former Soviet republic.
	   ``Taking into account that Egypt is one of the most influential
countries in North Africa and the Arab world, there is every reason
to believe that close economic relations with Egypt can help
Belarus develop relations with other countries in the region,''
Kozik said.
	   (str/ls) 	   
