<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Spain-Child Murders </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
German doctor convicted of murdering his two young children in
</HEADLINE>
Spanish resort &QL; 
 &UR; With AP Photo MAD105 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   PALMA DE MALLORCA, Spain (AP) _ A German doctor was convicted
Thursday of murdering his two young children while vacationing on
the Spanish resort island of Mallorca in September 1996.
	   Dr. Ruedeger Oyntzen admitted to injecting his 8-year-old
daughter and 6-year-old son with a lethal dose of tranquilizers
when he was arrested, just hours after the children's bodies were
found in their beds in a hotel.
	   The jury in the trial that began June 1 rejected the defense's
argument that the doctor suffered from a personality disorder that
diminished his responsibility for the deaths.
	   Oyntzen had taken his children for a two-week vacation to the
sunny Mediterranean island off the northeastern Spanish coast
shortly after losing a custody battle with his estranged wife in
the German courts.
	   After his arrest the 40-year-old radiologist from Breisach,
Germany, said the loss of custody had prompted him to kill his
children.
	   The prosecution seeks a 40-year jail term, while the defense is
hoping that Oyntzen's immediate confession will cut this by over
half, the national news agency EFE reported.
	   Defense lawyer Carlos Portalo said he and his client are waiting
for the presiding judge to hand down the sentence, at an as yet
unspecified date, before they decide whether to appeal.
	   (jt)
</TEXT>
