<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-DFS Classic, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Graf wins second match of comeback
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS Steffi quotes in 8th graf, updates &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BIRMINGHAM, England (AP) _ Steffi Graf took just one hour to
beat Kristie Boogert in straight sets Thursday and advance to the
quarterfinals of the DFS Classic.
	   In her second match in four months, the former world No. 1
player dominated the Dutch qualifier 6-2, 6-4 on another
rain-slowed day at Edgbaston.
	   The top-seeded Graf, wearing warmup pants on a cold and overcast
day, looked sharper than the previous day when she needed three
sets to beat Australia's Rennae Stubbs.
	   Graf is playing in only her third tournament since undergoing
knee surgery a year ago. She is preparing for Wimbledon _ which
starts June 22 _ a tournament she has won seven times.
	   The winner of 21 Grand Slams got a chuckle when told British
bookmakers had made her 4-1 second favorite behind Martina Hingis
to win the Wimbledon crown.
	   ``We'll see,'' she said. ``I do feel confident going into the
tournament but now it's too far ahead to think about winning it.''
	   Graf said her game was more settled Thursday and she was
enjoying tennis playing tennis again after the surgery and nagging
injuries.
	   ``I am serving a bit better but I still have a lot of improving
to do in that department,'' she said.
	   Graf took the first set in 28 minutes with breaks in the third
and seventh games and raced to a 3-0 lead in the second set.
Boogert won three straight games to even the set at 3-3 before Graf
regained command.
	   Graf will meet eighth-seed Magui Serna in the quarterfinals, the
Spaniard advancing after a straight sets win over American Corina
Morariu.
	   Second-seeded Irina Spirlea had to wait four days to play her
first match of the tournament but took just 63 minutes to beat
Canada's Maureen Drake 6-4, 6-2 and advance to the third round.
	   In other third round play, 1997 champion Nathalie Tauziat, of
France, beat Italy's Rita Grande 6-3, 6-0.
	   (scw)	   
</TEXT>
