	   THE price on the Kuala Lumpur Tin Market continued to rise and
was 16 sen up yesterday to RM23.82 per kg on the sustained strength
of the overnight price on the London Metal Exchange (LME).
	   The tin price on the LME was up US$75 per tonne.
	   With prices soaring, sellers were holding on to their stocks
while buyers, who comprised mainly Europeans and locals, bid for
more of the metal, dealers said.
	   At the opening level, buyers bid for 102 tonnes while sellers
offered only 66 tonnes.
	   Turnover declined to 66 tonnes from 74 tonnes yesterday.
	   
