Prosecutor says corruption main threat to Russian security
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Corruption is one of the main threats to Russia's
national security, Prosecutor General Yuri Skuratov said Thursday.
	   Skuratov told Russian independent television NTV that corruption
was ``rather widespread'' on all government levels, from local to
federal.
	   If law-enforcement agencies continue to ignore the problem, it
could threaten the country's existence, the chief prosecutor said.
