	   TWENTY-FIVE participants of the World Cup France '98's Scavenger
Hunt contest organised by Canon Singapore Pte Ltd have been
selected as winners.
	   Fifteen winners will fly to France to watch the June 23 match
between Brazil and Norway scheduled to kick off at Stade Velodrome
in Marseille, while the remaining 10 will watch the Spain-Bulgaria
match on June 24 at Stade Geoffroy-Guichard in St Etienne.
	   The winners comprise 14 Internet surfers from Malaysia, six from
Singapore, three from Hong Kong, and one each from Thailand and
Australia.
	   The contest, which was opened to Asian football fans, required
participants to answer 60 true-or-false questions about Canon and
its products.
	   The questions were posted through the Canon Singapore Web site
at www.canon.com.sg.
	   The lucky draw was conducted in Singapore on May 5. Canon is one
of the main sponsors for France '98, which officially kicked off
yesterday with reigning champions Brazil taking on Scotland at
Stade de France in St Denis.
	   
</TEXT>
