<HEADLINE>
Create `air of carnival' for Games, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Create `air of carnival' for Games, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Sager AhmadASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   DATUK Bandar Tan Sri Kamaruzzaman Sharif has asked the Kuala
Lumpur Tourist Association to create a carnival atmospehere in the
city between Sept 11 and 21 to promote the 16th Commonwealth Games.
	   He said association (KLTA) members who were hoteliers could play
a leading role in this effort.
	   ``During the games, the city will have an influx of foreigners
and we would like everyone especially organisations such as the
KLTA, which has a lot of experience, to promote Kuala Lumpur.
	   ``Tourism is a money spinner and the KLTA should help turn Kuala
Lumpur into a major tourist destination and a shopping haven by
embarking on more aggresive campaigns,'' he said.
	   Kamaruzzaman, also the patron of the 35-year-old association,
praised KLTA member the Taxi, Hired Car and Limousing Operators
Association of West Pahang, Federal Territory and Selangor
(Perpekli) for distributing 200,000 pamphlets on the dos and don'ts
when using taxis.
	   Perpekli president Aslah Abdullah said public response has been
encouraging towards taxi use after the launching of the pamphlets
by Entrepreneur Development Minister Datuk Mustapa Mohamed in
March.
	   Kamaruzzaman had earlier received new KLTA executive committee
members led by its new chairman Jamaliah Aris who called on him at
his office in Jalan Raja Laut. They were elected during the KLTA
annual meeting on April 29.
	   Jamaliah said KLTA would be participating in several programmes
this year including the KLTA Vision Four Florathon '98 on June 28,
Floral Parade on July 5, and Florex '98 - Floriculture Exhibition
between July 9 and 12.
	   She said the KLTA Vision Four Florathon '98 would be flagged off
at the Dataran Merdeka at 7.30am and was open to the public.
	   ``It will involve a two-km walk along Dataran Merdeka and the
Lake Gardens in your best floral togs and merit is given to
flower-power and not speed.
	   ``Participants from all ages can expect to walk away with
fabulous prizes.
	   ``The theme is Games &AMP; Pastimes and participation fee for both
the national and international categories are: individual (adult) -
RM12; children below 12 - RM6; family (maximum of five) - RM50;
senior citizen - RM6; and company - RM100,'' she said.
	   Jamaliah said last year's event attracted 800 participants
including foreign tourists.
	   She said KLTA would also be participating in the Floral Parade
this year, to be held between 8am and 10am on July 5 at te Dataran
Merdeka.
	   She said KLTA would also be organising a four-day Florex '98 -
Floriculture Exhibition at the Amcorp Mall in Petaling Jaya from
July 9.
	   She said it was a significant and important flower exposition
which would be an excellent platform for exhibitors in the
floriculture and horticulture industries to promote their products
and services.
	   Visitors to the exhibition will be able to view flowers, greens,
landscaping services, floriculture equipment, floral accessories,
tissue cultures, green/glass houses, bonsai and publications.
	   For details on Florathon '98, call Kay or Roslin at 03-284 2788
or fax 03-2825788.
	   
</TEXT>
