<HEADLINE>
House passes new entertainment Bill, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
House passes new entertainment Bill, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE House yesterday passed the Entertainment and Places of
Entertainment Enactment 1997 which provides for the licensing and
regulation of entertainment and places of public entertainment in
the State.
	   With the implementation of the Bill, the Theatres and Places of
Public Amusement Enactment 1958 will cease to be in force.
	   In tabling the Bill, Chief Minister Tan Sri Dr Koh Tsu Koon
(BN-Tanjung Bunga) said although the basic features of the existing
Enactment were retained in the Bill, it however sought to define in
greater detail the activities to be controlled.
	   ``It also seeks to provide for heavier penalties for offences
committed under the proposed Enactment.''
	   Koh said the existing enactment was enforced since December 1958
although ``the form of entertainment and entertainment places had
since changed and involve a much wider scope.'' Also, he said,
places of entertainment for the public had increased.
	   ``Which is why it is necessary to control and enforce such
activities.
	   Furthermore, entertainment outlets have been identified as one
of the sources of social ills,'' he said.
	   Koh said the new Bill would seek to confer upon authorised
officers powers of enforcement which, under the existing Enactment,
were only conferred on police officers.
	   It however contains provisions for the exemption of action
against entertainment held for religious, educational,
recreational, social, welfare, and charitable purposes.
	   
</TEXT>
