	   THE popular PC Game Challenge will make an appearance yet again
at the coming PC Fair '98 cash-and-carry event.
	   The competition, organised by IT Publications Sdn Bhd (ITP),
promises to be an exciting platform for local ``speed demons'' to
show off their racing skills, albeit interactively.
	   This year, five vendors - Microsoft (M) Sdn Bhd, Acer Sales and
Services Sdn Bhd, Summit Company (M) Sdn Bhd, Electronic Arts and
Vertex International Trading - are teaming up to provide gamers
with what could be the ultimate challenge.
	   Electronic Arts will be hosting the PC Game Challenge on a daily
basis throughout the three-day fair with its Need for Speed II car
racing title.
	   Vertex has agreed to contribute seven units of its Rockfire
Daredevil Realistic racing wheels.
	   To complete the gaming environment set-up, Acer Malaysia is
providing 10 multimedia Pentium-based personal computers.
	   The peripherals and computers will be distributed throughout the
three PC Fair locations. All the winners stand to win attractive
prizes.
	   Microsoft Malaysia is giving away 10 units of its Office 98
suite, while Summit is sponsoring 18 compact disk units featuring
such titles as Rebel Moon Rising, Mageslayer and Sega-Manx TT.
Electronic Arts has donated 38 units of hot titles such as Armoured
Fist 2.0, Galapagos, Fifa Soccer Manager, Darklight Conflict,
Scarab, and of course, the World Cup '98.
	   Vertex is sponsoring three units of the Rockfire Daredevil
Realistic racing wheels (ergonomically-designed wheel with 180
steering radius), and six units of the Rockfire Galaxy Fighter IR
joysticks (the world's first analogue infrared remote control
flightstick).
	   PC Fair is organised by the Association of the Computer Industry
Malaysia (Pikom).
	   
</TEXT>
