<SLUG> PROJECTS-DENIED-BOI sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Projects denied BoI privileges, NATION
</HEADLINE>
Projects denied BoI privileges, NATION &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NATION
   THAILAND
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE Board of Investment Wednesday turned down applications for
promotional privileges for a Bt93 billion project by Bangkok
Expressway Plc (BECL) and a Bt3 billion water pipeline project by
East Water Resources Development and Management Plc.
	   PM's Office Minister Abhisit Vejjajiva, who oversees the BoI,
said the board chaired by Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai did not
grant investment privileges to BECL's project as it was not a new
scheme, just an extension of the second stage expressway project
from Asoke to Srinakharin Road.
	   BECL was awarded a 30-year concession contract to operate the
second stage expressway project by Expressway and Rapid Transit
Authority of Thailand (ETA) in December 1988. The project was later
integrated with the first-stage expressway. Besides the privileges,
BECL also asked the government to raise toll fees in September. In
the first quarter, the company recorded a Bt134 million loss,
having suffered from foreign exchange losses and a higher interest
burden.
	   Abhisit said the board rejected East Water's water pipeline
project as it is a state enterprise with the Provincial Waterworks
Authority as majority shareholder. Moreover, it is a monopoly
operator in the area.
	   Meanwhile, the BoI has extended privileges to three new
industries -- logistics, crops grown by hydroponics and
engines/auto parts repair.
	   BoI secretary general Staporn Kavitanon said logistics is an
efficient system to lower the cost of goods transportation. The
system is popular in the auto, retailing and courier sectors.
	   There is no constraint on foreign shareholding for logistics
companies providing an international service or located in the
industrial promotion Zone 3. The investors will receive maximum
privileges on imported machinery without any condition on location,
while corporate tax privileges will depend on the industrial
promotional zone.
	   The hydroponics system is an advanced plantation technology with
lower production cost and water usage. It will help farmers grow
agricultural products other than seasonal crops.
	   For the engines/auto parts repair business, the investor will
receive privileges on imported machinery without a plant location
requirement, but it must export all products.
	   Staporn said the board also granted privileges to the Bt2.5
billion Polyester products manufacturer of Indo Polyester
(THailand) Co Ltd which will hire 135 workers and is expected to
earn Bt1.13 billion in foreign exchange a year.
	   
</TEXT>
