<HEADLINE>
Jalan Gasing issue to be discussed, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Jalan Gasing issue to be discussed, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PETALING Jaya Selatan MP Donald Lim said Jalan Gasing residents
would meet Petaling Jaya Municipal Council officials today to
discuss their unhappiness over the widening of the road.
	   Residents are expected to hear answers to issues raised in a
memorandum sent to the MPPJ recently.
	   ``According to residents, they were not consulted before the
project began. Residents feel that after the road has been widened,
those living in adjacent houses will find it difficult to drive out
of their homes,'' he told the New Straits Times after visiting the
Seri Setia Old Folk's Home in Seri Setia.
	   ``I understand their anger as they were not consulted. According
to MPPJ, the road is too narrow and heavily used. Therefore, there
was a need to widen it.''
	   The council also planned to cover drains along the road to
prevent water from overflowing.
	   The project is expected to be completed by the end of the year.
	   Meanwhile, Lim said Section 5 residents were receiving water
from MPPJ as scheduled.
	   He said the situation has improved since residents protested
against poor water supply last month.
	   He said MPs, NGOs, residents and consumer associations would
meet Selangor Menteri Besar Datuk Abu Hassan Omar on June 25 to
discuss problems due to inadequate water supply.
	   ``It is a good thing that the State Government is having the
meeting. It will give an opportunity to NGOs and associations to
present their views.
	   ``The rationing programme is not working. It has never followed
the schedule.
	   ``At this meeting, we hope a new plan will be formulated.''
	   
