<HEADLINE>
Jail, rotan for sodomy, attempted murder, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Jail, rotan for sodomy, attempted murder, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   MALACCA, Wed. - A welder, who admitted sodomising a 12-year-old
boy he had attempted to kill, was sentenced to a total of 16 years'
jail by the Sessions Court today.
	   Tan Kiam Huat, 36, of Lorong Selamat, Georgetown, Penang, who
pleaded guilty to three charges of sodomy, attempted murder and
illegally confining the boy, was also ordered to receive three
strokes of the rotan.
	   The offences were committed in an abandoned housing lot behind
Anglo- Chinese School in Tengkera on May 20.
	   Judge Halijah Abbas sentenced Tan to: 10 years' jail and three
strokes for sodomy; a year's jail for illegally confining the boy;
and, five years' jail for attempting to murder the boy by forcing
him into a sewerage tank. The sentences will run consecutively.
	   
</TEXT>
