<HEADLINE>
Order against anti-car theft gadget producer, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Order against anti-car theft gadget producer, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Wed. - The High Court today ordered a company and
three others to stop manufacturing an anti-theft car gadget on
grounds that they were not its copyright owners.
	   Judge Datuk R.K. Nathan said the copyright in the form of all
information and trade secrets of the device belonged to Australian
companies, Electro Cad Australia Pty Ltd and Stopcard Pty Ltd
(Australia).
	   In making the order, he directed Mejati RCS Sdn Bhd, Lai Kar
Fatt, V- Kool (M) Sdn Bhd and Central Monitoring System Sdn Bhd to
stop manufacturing, distributing or selling their gadget under the
brand name ``Stopcar''.
	   He held that the gadget possessed features identical to that
manufactured by the Australians under the name ``Stopcard''.
	   The plaintiffs had claimed that the defendants were producing
the device based on information and trade secrets obtained from
them.
	   The device enables the owner of a car to stop the engine of his
car by just dialing a number in his telephone and another procedure
is needed to re-start the car.
	   The Australians said their device, Stopcard Auto Theft Device
(Stopcard) and the Malaysian-made ``Stopcar'' were identical as
both had the same functions and worked on the same system.
	   Nathan, in allowing a claim by Electro Cad, Stopcard and
Stopcard (M) Sdn Bhd, also stopped the defendants from passing off
``Stopcar'' as the product of the plaintiffs and from divulging or
using any information obtained from the plaintiffs.
	   
</TEXT>
