<HEADLINE>
Acer PCs for Game Challenge, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Acer PCs for Game Challenge, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   I-Mei LowASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   VISITORS trying their luck in the Ultimate Need for Speed II PC
Game Challenge at the PC Fair '98 cash-and-carry event will have
plenty of computing power at their control.
	   Acer Sales and Services (M) Sdn Bhd will sponsor 10 units of its
popular AcerEntra 3000 desktops for participants of the game.
	   The AcerEntra 3000, a 233-megahertz Internet-ready Pentium MMX
machine, comes with 32-speed CD-ROM, 3.2-gigabyte (GB) Ultra DMA
hard disk drive, 512-kilobyte (KB) L2 pipeline burst cache memory
and 32-megabyte (MB) synchronous dynamic random access memory
(SDRAM).
	   For better sound and more striking graphics, the computers also
come with a 15-inch digital monitor, stereo sound speakers, 16-bit
three- dimensional (3-D) sound cards and a 2MB 64-bit
three-dimensional (3-D) graphics accelerator card.
	   For those who may not have time to take part in the competition,
look out for Acer's new series of notebooks, the Acer Extensa 710
which will be on display. The notebooks are priced from RM7,000 to
RM10,000.
	   
</TEXT>
