	   IPOH, Wed. - The State Umno has appointed Teluk Intan division
chief Che Onn Hamzah and Sungai Siput division head Datuk Mohd
Padil Harun to debate on the resolutions at the party general
assembly in Kuala Lumpur.
	   Its chief Tan Sri Ramli Ngah Talib said Che Onn would represent
the State Umno in debating the resolution on the economy while Mohd
Padil would speak during the debate on the presidential address.
	   This was decided at the committee meeting at his residence this
afternoon. The three-day assembly starts on June 19.
	   The Menteri Besar also said in view of the prolonged economic
problems, the committee felt it should explain the situation to the
grassroots.
	   This was necessary to prevent them from being influenced by
undesirable elements out to confuse the people.
	   The party Information Committee had been entrusted with the
responsibility of explaining the matter to the people.
	   
