	   THE THAI American Student Exchange is now taking applications
for Thai and other foreign nationals to spend one year in the US
living with and helping as childcare workers to children of more
than 6,500 American host families who engage our helpers each year.
	   Asian girls, ages 18 to 26, with previous childcare experience
and/or training, strong English language proficiency, a drivers
licence, and non smoking, may apply to participate in the one-year
cultural exchange programme.
	   Benefits of the programme for those selected include: airflight
to the US; a four-day pre-departure orientation and training
programme in New York; an allowance of $140-200 per week paid by
host family; free room and board; health and accident insurance;
tuition for part-time bachelor/master degree courses; one month
travel opportunity upon completion of the programme; supervisory
support from the programme field staff and head office.
	   Qualifying exams and interviews will be given to applicants at
the office of Thai American Student Exchange, The Mall Two
Ramkamheng, tel 319 5901; Phone during office hours to make an
appointment for the test and interview.
	   Yoga training course at Wongsanit Ashram Wongsanit Ashram is
organising a training course on ''Yoga as a Tool for Healthy
Lifestyle'' from June 19-21 at the Ashram in Nakhon Nayok.
	   Registration fee is Bt1,650 which includes food, accommodation
and transportation.
	   For details, call 950 6601-3.
	   Chance to study at Ohio University The Graduate School, Bangkok
University, is now taking applications for doctoral degree courses
in Interpersonal Communication. This international programme is a
joint academic venture with Ohio University, US.
	   Students will have a chance to study at Ohio University, Athens
for two academic semesters. Application forms are available from
now until June 19. Master's degree holders in any field are
eligible.
	   For further information, please call 671 7508-9 or 350 3500 ext
508, 509, 611, or visit the website at http://www.bu.ac.th Foreign
Policy to be scrutinised Thammasat University's Faculty of
Political Science is holding a seminar on ''Foreign Policy of
Thailand during the Economic and Social Crisis'' on Friday (June
12), from 9 am to noon, on the fourth floor meeting room of the
multi-purpose building.
	   The speakers are Foreign Affairs Minister Surin Pitsuwan, Kobsak
Chutikul, Nipon Poapongsakorn, Tarnthong Thongsawad, Kavi
Chongkittavorn, while Khajit Jitseri will act as moderator.
Admission is free and everyone is welcome.
	   Learn method to paint baked clay Robinson Department Store in
co-oporation with Art Training Centre is running a weekend course
of ''Baked Clay Painting'' on Saturday and Sunday (June 13-14) at
Robinson Bang Khae.
	   On June 20 and June 21, there will be a course on ''Colourful
Fantasy Candles'' and ''Making Fancy Necklace from FIMO''.
	   Thos interested can apply for the courses at PR Counter,
Robinson Lat Yah, Bang Khae, and Fashion Island, or call for
details at 248 2626 ext 1000, 1033, 1928. Each course is limited to
only 20 participants.
	   
