<HEADLINE>
Costa Rica's Marin upsets Argentina's Gumy in Bologna tennis
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; RETRANSMITTING to uppercase dateline

<TEXT>
	   BOLOGNA, Italy (AP)_ Costa Rican Juan Antonio Marin upset Hernan
Gumy of Argentina 6-4, 6-2 on Thursday in the second round of the
dlrs 340,000 Carisbo International Tennis Tournament.
	   Gumy's loss came just two days after his own upset defeat of the
tournament's No. 1 seed, Alberto Berasategui.
	   As for Marin, he said his victory was no surprise. ``I always
believed in it,'' he told reporters.
	   In other play Thursday, Italian Marzio Martelli defeated Juan
Albert Viloca of Spain 6-3, 6-3 and Mariano Puerta of Argentina
defeated Emillio Alvarez of Spain 5-7, 7-6 (6), 6-3 Thursday.
	   (cph)
