	   KUALA TERENGGANU, Wed. - A 14-year-old schoolgirl who was
reported missing in Kuala Ibai three days ago was found drowned in
a river this morning.
	   Villagers found the body of Masrinoor Abdul Rahman, a pupil of
Sekolah Menengah Agama Khairiah, floating in the Sungai Tok Molor
about 8am.
	   Kuala Terengganu police deputy chief Superintendent Tajudin
Ahmad said the deceased was last seen leaving home for tuition on
Sunday about 5.30pm.
	   
