<HEADLINE>
Project to boost freshwater fish supply, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Project to boost freshwater fish supply, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA BARU, Wed. - Kelantan can expect increased supply of
freshwater fish after the State Fisheries Department releases
several species of fish fry at three locations beginning this
month.
	   Its director Sani Mohd Isa said the department chose three
rivers in two districts for the project.
	   The rivers were Sungai Pasir Era and Sungai Lata Rek, both in
Kuala Krai and Sungai Kelantan in Kemubu, he said.
	   He added that the first release of fish fry would be in Sungai
Lata Rek at the end of the month.
	   He said the project, launched earlier this year, aimed to
replenish the population of freshwater fish in its natural habitat.
	   ``The department has an allocation of RM15,000 to buy fish fry
as well as freshwater prawns this year,'' he added.
	   He said the project would not only help supplement fishermen's
income but also boost local fish production.
	   He encouraged more people to rear freshwater fish as the returns
were good.
	   
