of women headed straight for the grave site at Kazan cemetery in
Srebrenica.
	   In the summer of 1995, in one of the worst incidents of ethnic
cleansing in the Bosnian war, Bosnian Serb troops overran the
Muslim enclave in eastern Bosnia.
