w1773 &Cx1f; wstm-
r w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  MOTOROLA-PURCHASESsked     06-11 0470
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> MOTOROLA-PURCHASES sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Motorola purchases set to hit RM1b, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Motorola purchases set to hit RM1b, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   MOTOROLA Malaysia Sdn Bhd expects its annual purchases from its
string of local component suppliers to reach a total value of RM1
billion in the year 2000, compared to RM785 million last year.
	   The company said this in a statement issued yesterday to
announce its participation at the SMI Showcase 98 - Electrical &AMP;
Electronics and Telecommunications which will be held at the Putra
World Trade Centre from June 25 to 29.
	   To date, Motorola sources from more than 100 local suppliers,
various types of components ranging from semiconductor lead frames,
flexible circuit boards, LCD, precision tooling, engineering
plastic parts and packaging.
	   Also, it has another 500 local partners which supply and service
the company's daily factory maintenance, repairs and operational
requirements for each of its five manufacturing facilities in
Selangor, Penang and Seremban.
	   ``Local sourcing to Motorola means we will actively develop
local suppliers and provide overall support to them in technology,
management and training.
	   ``This investment helps them become our preferred suppliers
besides raising their technical level, allowing them to expand
their growth in other directions,'' vice-president and country
manager Ramli Abbas said.
	   The SMI Showcase 98, organised by the Small and Medium
Industries Development Corporation, will exhibit the goods and
services offered by the country's SMIs.
	   It also has another feature namely the ``Apec Cross Border
Linkages''
	   which provides opportunities to participating companies to match
their businesses with those of visiting companies from Apec
countries.
	   Motorola said eight local companies which it has helped to
develop into major OEM suppliers will also be exhibiting its wares
at the SMI Showcase 98.
	   These companies are BCM Electronics Corporation Sdn Bhd, PMM
Components Sdn Bhd, Precision Tool Tech Sdn Bhd, QDOS Flexcircuits
Sdn Bhd, Semiconductor Assembler and Manufacturer Sdn Bhd, Statsym
Sdn Bhd, The Sand Pipers Sdn Bhd, and Wong Engineering Corporation
Bhd.
	   
</TEXT>
