IBM launches new S/390 G5 enterprise-class server, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Ferina ManeckshaASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   IBM World Trade Corp has expanded its mainframe offerings with
the launch of the new System/390 Generation 5 (S/390 G5)
enterprise-class server, which is designed to be double the
performance of previous models.
	   The S/390 G5 performs at more than 900 million instructions per
second when configured with 10 microprocessors. Users needing
larger systems can deploy IBM's S/390 Parallel Sysplex clustering
technology. ``The S/390 continues to define the standard in
enterprise computing. It can handle unpredictable workloads and
bring customers the advantage of 30 years of technology leadership
integrated with advanced computing capabilities,''
	   said IBM Malaysia's country market manager for S/390, storage
and printers, Tang Hang Kwang.
	   
