<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Puerto Rico-Weather-Urban and Small Stream Flood </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Advisory,0242
</HEADLINE>

BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY
NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
359 PM AST THU JUN 11 1998

...THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN SAN JUAN PR HAS ISSUED AN URBAN
   AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY EFFECTIVE UNTIL 600 PM FOR
   THE INTERIOR AND WEST SECTIONS OF PUERTO RICO FROM UTUADO WEST TO
   ANASCO...MOCA...AGUADA AND RINCON...

A CLUSTER OF SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS...SOME WITH VERY HEAVY
RAINS...HAVE DEVELOPED ACROSS THE INTERIOR AND WEST SECTIONS OF
PUERTO RICO. THESE STORMS WERE DEVELOPING OVER UTUADO AND MOVING
SLOWLY WETS THROUGH MOCA...SAN SEBASTIAN...ANASCO...AGUADA AND
RINCON. DOPPLER RADAR ESTIMATES INDICATED UP TO THREE INCHES AN
HOURS IN BARRIOS CERRO GORDO...HUMATAS AND ESPINO IN ANASCO.
SIMILAR AMOUNTS WERE INDICATED ACROSS THE INTERIOR SECTIONS OF THE
ISLAND FROM UTUADO WESTWARD. FLOODING OF STREETS...ROADS AND LOW
LYING AREAS ARE LIKELY IN THE ADVISORY AREA. MUDSLIDES ARE ALSO
POSSIBLE IN THESE AREAS.

MOTORISTS AND PEDESTRIANS IN OR PASSING THROUGH THE ADVISORY AREA
...ESPECIALLY ROAD # 2...THIS AFTERNOON SHOULD AVOID CROSSING FLOODED
ROADS...AND ALLOW EXTRA TIME TO REACH THEIR DESTINATIONS.
REMEMBER...CARS CAN EASILY STALL IN THE WATER AND BE CARRIED AWAY IN
ANY CURRENT. PEDESTRIANS ARE ALSO ADVISED TO STAY AWAY FROM RISING
WATER.
 &HT;    
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Puerto Rico-Weather-Urban and Small Stream Flood Advisory; CT:w; 
(REG:CRB;)
(REG:ENGL;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
)

