	   Rushdy Hasan Belbasy, an associate of a murdered Yemeni man,
denied yesterday that he was being sought by the police in
connection with the slaying.
	   ``I was summoned to the city police headquarters in my capacity
only as a witness in the case,'' Rushdy said in a statement faxed
to The Jakarta Post.
	   ``I am not running away and I have left my address with the
police.''
	   The body of the Yemeni, identified as Hasan Muhammad Yeslam, 26,
was discovered at Hotel Pitagiri in Palmerah, West Jakarta, Monday
morning.
	   The victim was found with a neck wound at about 6 a.m. in a room
by a hotel security guard.
	   City police spokesman Lt. Col. E. Aritonang said yesterday the
case was still under investigation.
	   ``Yes, it is all being examined thoroughly. We do not have any
suspects yet but wait for the examination results for more
information,'' he said. 
