MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   A prosecutor asked Tangerang district court to sentence Sopan
Tarigan, 36, to 30 months in jail for attempting to smuggle 25,750
Ecstasy pills and a quantity of the drug in powdered form through
Soekarno-Hatta International Airport.
	   Prosecutor Sity Zahara said in her indictment that the defendant
was arrested by customs and excise officers on Aug. 31 last year
when he collected a black bag from the airport.
	   Officers found the pills and powder in the bag. Sopan claimed he
was asked by a man called Achmadi Surya to collect the bag and did
not know what it contained, she said. Achmadi is still at large.
	   ``Sopan said that he was paid Rp 40,000 to collect the bag and
was also promised a job,'' Sity said.
	   The defendant was charged under Article 62 of Law No.5/1997 on
psychotropic drugs. The article carries a maximum sentence of five
years in jail and a fine of Rp 100 million.
	   Judge Jesminar Idrus adjourned the trial until next week to hear
the defense lawyer's statement. 
</TEXT>
