<HEADLINE>
Premiere to raise funds for cancer patients, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Premiere to raise funds for cancer patients, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Wed. - Watch a movie and contribute to a
much-needed fund that will help save cancer patients.
	   The appeal comes from the National Cancer Council (Makna) which
is now organising a charity premiere, City of Angels, on June 14.
	   Reacting to the call, Crown Princess Inter-Continental Kuala
Lumpur will issue 200 Crown Princess privileged cards to those who
buy the RM150 tickets for the show.
	   The cards will enable them get 20 per cent discount at any of
the six restaurants at the hotel.
	   Its regional communication manager Audrey Lim presented a mock
card to Makna chief executive officer Datuk P. Venugopal at Balai
Berita today.
	   Also present was Makna project manager Farahida Mohd Farid.
	   ``Every year without fail, we try to reach out to the disabled,
orphaned and those in need of aid. I believe that we should give
them a hand whenever we can,'' she said.
	   Venugopal said any form of contribution would go a long way in
helping the council to provide a better health care system,
especially in the prevention and control of cancer.
	   ``Proceeds will go towards our efforts to help people get access
to information and treatment against cancer,'' he said.
	   Sales of tickets have brought in RM25,000 so far.
	   Featuring Academy Award winner Nicolas Cage and two-time Golden
Globe nominee Meg Ryan, the story is about the romance between a
no-nonsense surgeon and an angel. Directed by Brad Silberling, Cage
plays restless angel Seth who, on duty in Los Angeles, encounters
Dr Maggie Rice (Ryan), a heart surgeon who is deeply shaken after
losing a patient on the operating table.
	   To be held at the UE3 Mall, Cheras, it aims to raise about
RM75,000.
	   The council's patron Datin Seri Dr Wan Azizah Wan Ismail, who is
also the wife of Deputy Prime Minister Datuk Seri Anwar Ibrahim,
will attend the premiere.
	   The event is being held with the assistance of Warner Brothers
(M) Sdn Bhd, the UE3 Mall and UA Sdn Bhd, which operates four
cineplexes in the mall with a total capacity of 1,337 seats.
	   Tickets can be obtained by calling 03-4569178/9, faxing
03-4569203 or e- mailing makna &LR; po.jaring.my.
	   
