<HEADLINE>
A notebook providing all-in-one convenience, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
A notebook providing all-in-one convenience, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Fauziah MuhtarASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE ThinkPad notebook computer from International Business
Machines Corp has been in the market for quite some time now. It's
common nowadays to see a business professional sitting down at a
corner in a hotel lobby, operating his notebook, oblivious to the
people around him.
	   The ThinkPad is an impressive portable tool. Over the years, IBM
has managed to incorporate innovative technologies into this sleek
machine, making it one of the better products in the market.
	   There are a few models available in the ThinkPad series. An
addition to the series is the ThinkPad 380XD which is actually not
an entirely new product. The significant feature that
differentiates ThinkPad 380XD from other previous models is its
all-in-one drive.
	   However, this is not something very new as several notebook
manufacturers have already introduced the feature.
	   There are many modular designed notebooks and sub-notebooks
which allow us to swap the drive component from compact disk (CD)
to floppy, or hook an additional drive for the subs. But in the
ThinkPad 380XD, everything is integrated, including the CD, floppy
and hard disk.
	   This means that you don't have to carry around your CD drive and
swap it with your floppy drive when the need arises. In other
words, you don't have to lug around extra weight, or worry about
leaving a drive behind.
	   The bundled drives include a four-gigabyte (GB) hard disk,
3.5-inch internal diskette drive and a 10-speed CD-ROM drive. The
three drives are stacked up on one another on the right side of the
notebook.
	   The ThinkPad 380XD is configured with a 233-megahertz (MHz)
Intel Pentium processor with MMX technology, 4GB of S.M.A.R.T. hard
drive and a standard 32-megabyte random access memory (RAM)
expandable to 96MB with 512KB Level 2 (L2) cache, which promises
satisfactory multimedia performance for its compact casing.
	   Its sight capability is projected through the 12.1-inch
thin-film transistor (TFT) screen that is able to support 16
million colours of 800 by 600 resolution. To ensure satisfactory
video presentations, the motion picture experts group (MPEG) 1
support is incorporated with peripheral component interconnect
(PCI) bus enhancement.
	   The ThinkPad 380XD is designed with Sound Blaster Pro support,
integrated stereo speakers located in front of the notebook and a
microphone. At the back of the notebook are two serial ports; one
is parallel and the other is universal serial bus (USB).
	   A PS/2 port is available together with an extension for the
optional Port Replicator to deliver impressive performance in the
office or on the road.
	   On the left-hand side, you will find the headphone and
microphone jacks, volume control, the personal computer memory card
international association (PCMCIA) slot and the battery.
	   Like most notebook designs, the light emitting diodes (LEDs) are
located on top of the keyboard for displaying the notebook status.
Its rather novel input device, the red accupoint, can be found
in-between the keys.
	   The brightness control for the screen is beside the screen
itself.
	   Other than the pre-loaded Windows 95 operating system, users
will be given Lotus SmartSuite application as a bonus offering.
	   For more information on IBM bundled software, a ThinkPad
Software Select is available on the notebook. This feature is,
however, shipped uninstalled on the new ThinkPad.
	   These applications which will assist users in administering and
managing their systems are listed on the left-hand frame of this
page.
	   The software included are IBM AntiVirus, IBM Client Services for
Netfinity, Intel LANDesk Client Manager and Tivoli TME10
Lightweight Client Framework.
	   The ThinkPad 380XD is powered by a lithium-ion battery which is
said to last about three-and-a-half to four-and-a-half hours.
	   This model also comes standard with a one-year international
limited warranty.
	   
</TEXT>
