WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE biggest star at the recent Electronic Entertainment Expo
(E3) in Atlanta, US, was actress Gillian Anderson, the FBI agent
Scully in The X- Files. She was present to promote Fox
Interactive's spin-off game which also stars actor David Duchovny,
better known as agent Mulder.
	   Anderson confessed to a lapsed love of computer games. ``Years
ago, I played Tetris, Tortured Souls and Myst. Just a bit though. I
am terrified of delving into some other reality that I am not able
to come out of and forgetting I am a mother with responsibilities
in my life,'' she says. ``I have requested a lot of CD-ROMs -
educational, dictionaries and encylopaedia. They are there when I
have some time.''
	   
