<BODY>
<SLUG> ADVANTAGE-BRINGS-TALLY sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Advantage brings in latest Tally printers, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Advantage brings in latest Tally printers, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Fauziah MuhtarASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   ADVANTAGE Systems Sdn Bhd recently introduced seven new high-end
line and dot-matrix printers under the Tally brand to the local
market.
	   The new line printers are the T6140, T6141 and T6180, while the
dot- matrix models comprise the T2040, T2055, T2070 and T2070-2T.
	   Advantage's product manager for Tally printers and Axis products
William Ng claimed the T6180 is currently the world's fastest line
printer.
	   ``The T6180 is fast because it can print two rows at one time at
a speed of 1,800 lines per minute based on the shutter
technology,'' Ng said.
	   The model is designed with fast reduced instruction set
computing (RISC) controller featuring Page Segmentation
Architecture (PSA) which is designed to intelligently arrange data
into pages prior to printing. It handles six-part forms and prints
a line up to 136 columns wide at 10 characters per inch (cpi).
	   Ng said the printer is also able to produce uniform and solid
dot creation with the injection-moulded impact element.
	   The auto-switching parallel and serial interfaces come standard
with FourPlex and LANPlex. It also supports personal computers
(PCs), IBM mid- range and mainframe systems, and network printing
formats.
	   Two other models - the T6140 and T6141 - are able to print 1,420
lines per minute with 250,000 pages per month workload. The
difference between the two is the quiet cabinet design on the T6141
which emits less noise.
	   The Tally line printers, including the T6180, are equipped with
various software applications including one for printing barcode.
	   ``The significant feature about the Tally printers is that they
have more printer drivers (including Windows driver) than any other
line printer in the market,'' Ng said.
	   ``And compared to the older version of Tally printers, the new
range prints graphics faster.''
	   He said the T6140, T6141 and T6180 are designed for fast and
heavy-duty printing. They are considered to be suitable for use in
the banking, securities, corporate, manufacturing and government
sectors.
	   As for the T2040, it is a high-end dot matrix printer able to
handle 480 characters per second (cps) with 24 needles. It is a
front-feed machine with paper handling, paper park, and view and
tear point-of-sale (POS) applications.
	   The T2040 is intended for printing invoices, picking lists and
labels as well as licences, tickets, registration forms and cards.
	   Another two models - the T2055 and T2070 - are considered to be
Tally's fastest serial impact printers with 24 needles and
136-column printing.
	   They offer 730cps and 1,050cps printing speed respectively with
1,750 and 2,250 pages per day workload.
	   Both models have push tractors for continuous paper stock and
single sheet insertion for cut forms.
	   The T2070-2T has a second tractor to facilitate quick and easy
changing between two continuous paper stocks. Its straight paper
path ensures that the heavy forms and multi-part stock are
processed reliably.
	   Incorporation of the Automatic Gap Adjustment feature ensures
optimum print quality and reliable feeding of paper, Ng said.
	   Parallel and Serial RS232 interfaces are standard. For network,
it provides optional IBM Coax and Twinax interface.
	   According to Ng, Advantage sold about 300 units of the Tally
line printers by the middle of last year.
	   ``Out of these, the return rate was only five to eight per cent,
which indicates how reliable the printers were,'' he said.
	   He added that Advantage would be working with systems
integrators and business partners to push the printers.
	   The company expects about 100 units of the new printers to be
sold by the end of this year, with half going to its existing
customers and demand for the remaining half to come from new users.
	   ``To achieve this target, we will be sending flyers to customers
to tell them about such printers, inviting them for demos at our
showroom and educating them on the printers that really fit their
requirements,'' Ng said.
	   The Tally printers are estimated to have between 20 to 25 per
cent of the local line printer market at present.
	   Retail price of the T6180 is about RM55,000 while the T6140 and
T6141 are priced at around RM35,000.
	   
</TEXT>
