	   RATING Agency Malaysia Bhd (RAM) has reaffirmed the P2 rating
assigned to Kelang Port Management Sdn Bhd (KPM)'s Murabahah
underwritten notes issuance facility.
	   The rating agency said in a statement that despite the economic
slowdown which has negatively affected KPM's throughput and
revenue, the company's financial strength and strong balance sheet
will enable it to absorb the effects of the downturn without
adversely affecting its debt servicing ability.
	   RAM said the strength of KPM's shareholders - Kontena Nasional
Bhd (52.5 per cent), Malaysia International Shipping Corp (25 per
cent), Selangor State Government (12.5 per cent) and Lembaga
Urusuan Tabung Haji (10 per cent) - further enhances its risk
profile.
	   
