	   A firm bought some 25,000 tons US wheat for July shipment, an
industry source said yesterday.
	   ``The firm closed a deal for 25,000 tons of US wheat Saturday to
replenish its stocks,'' the source privy to the transaction said,
adding it was the first purchase the company undertook this year.
	   Most local flour millers had reduced their wheat orders since
the start of the year because of a slowdown in local flour
consumption arising from the weak peso.
	   The source said the Philippine flour mill plans to buy the same
quantity of wheat for August shipment if US prices fall from
current levels.
	   
