	   NEWBORN ... The Malacca Zoo in Ayer Keroh has a new ``star
attraction'' - a baby giraffe which was born early this month.
	   Zoo public relations officer Masri Arop said the baby giraffe,
weighing 25kg and standing 1.5 metres at birth, has been named
Ayah. Its parents are Anne and Masai.
	   There are three male and six female giraffes at the zoo.
	   Masri hoped companies would ``adopt'' the animals by taking care
of their upkeep. ``In spite of the economic slowdown, we hope
companies will continue sponsoring the animals.''
	   
