<HEADLINE>
Astro to raise DtU system fees, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Astro to raise DtU system fees, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Ariff AwangASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE price of the Astro Direct-to-U or DtU system will be
increased to RM1,199 from the present RM999, effective July 1 this
year.
	   In announcing the price increase, Astro executive director Mr
C.Y. Chin attributed it to the 60 per cent fall in the ringgit
since late last year.
	   He added that despite savings from lower manufacturing costs,
DtU systems are becoming increasingly costly.
	   ``Since the launch of the service, Astro has been subsidising
the DtU systems to make them more affordable to Malaysians,'' Chin
told reporters at Astro's briefing for the media and dealers in
Petaling Jaya yesterday.
	   He said the company has spent RM100 million on hardware
subsidies so far. Even with the new price, Astro will continue to
subsidise each DtU system heavily.
	   Astro's programming costs, he said, have also been rising.
However, Astro's monthly subscription of RM80 or RM2.67 per day
will remain to ensure the service remains affordable to as many
Malaysians as possible.
	   Since its launch in October 1996, Astro has added a number of
new value- added services at no additional cost to subscribers,
Chin said, adding that the new services include the premium sports
service, Astro SuperSport.
	   Astro currently has 185,000 subscribers nationwide who enjoy
access to 22 television channels (excluding TV1 and TV2) and eight
radio services, all digital, he said.
	   At the function Chin also announced that Astro will be giving
away over RM1 million in prizes and rewards to consumers and
dealers who take part in two nationwide contests.
	   
</TEXT>
