	   SHAH ALAM, Wed. - Menteri Besar Datuk Abu Hassan Omar today
announced changes in portfolios for all the State Executive
Councillors, except for himself and Dr Pius Martin.
	   He said no new portfolio was created and all the Exco members
would still hold two portfolios each while he continues to hold
five.
	   The changes take effect immediately.
	   He said, all those involved in the exercise, however retained
their core portfolio, except for Datuk Fuad Hassan who was given
two new portfolios.
	   Abu Hassan said he has already informed the Prime Minister Datuk
Seri Dr bu Hassan said: ``If they are not effective,
I will not change their portfolios but will just drop them.''
	   Abu Hassan also announced that Datin Paduka Rakibah Abdul Manap
would be on a three-month medical leave and her portfolio as the
State chairman on squatters would be held by Fuad while her other
portfolio will be held by Ch'ng Toh Eng.
	   
