<BODY>
<SLUG> GUAN-ENG-HELD-ASSEMBLY sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Guan Eng held for speaking at illegal assembly, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Guan Eng held for speaking at illegal assembly, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 11, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PETALING JAYA, Wed. - DAP deputy secretary-general Lim Guan Eng
was taken to the district police headquarters here tonight for
questioning for speaking at an illegal assembly.
	   The political secretary to DAP secretary-general Lim Kit Siang,
Hew Kuan Yow, Selangor DAP committee member Wong Kok Yew and party
member Lee Pin Soo were also picked up for allegedly obstructing
police from carrying out their duties.
	   Guan Eng, who is Kota Melaka MP, was picked up for questioning
after he spoke to about 1,000 party members at a solidarity dinner
at the Yat Yeh Hing restaurant in Jalan SS4D/2 about 10.30pm.
	   The police picked him up after repeatedly warning him and Kit
Siang not to speak since the gathering was held without a permit.
	   Police also moved in members of the Federal Reserve Unit's Light
Strike Force to disperse the crowd after they failed to heed the
police warning.
	   Present at the dinner were DAP national chairman Dr Chen Man Hin
and leaders Dr Tan Seng Giaw, Ahmad Nor, Dr Oon Hong Geok, Tan Kok
Wai, Teng Chang Khim, Ronnie Liu and Teresa Kok.
	   
</TEXT>
