	   THE Composite Index futures traded on the Kuala Lumpur Options
and Financial Futures Exchange (KLoffe) tracked the negative note
of the cash market to end lower yesterday.
	   Spot June ended 20.2 points lower to close at 488 with 2.903
lots traded while July futures lost 17.0 points to close at 485
with 295 lots changing hands.
	   Open interest for June and July stood at 18,792 lots and 1,892
lots respectively.
	   The September and December futures were not traded yesterday and
they settled at 494.1 and 501.1 respectively.
	   A dealer said the active selling of stocks in the cash market
which was prompted by the declining ringgit against the US dollar
led players to short the futures. He added that in view of the
downturn, it is difficult to see the upside potential for futures.
	   
