<HEADLINE>
Coyotes send Craig Janney to Tampa Bay for winger, draft pick
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PHOENIX (AP) _ The Phoenix Coyotes, who promised a shakeup after
another first-round playoff elimination, traded center Craig Janney
to the Tampa Bay Lightning on Thursday.
	   In return, the Coyotes received left wing Louie Debrusk and a
fifth-round pick in this summer's draft.
	   Janney, an 11-year pro acquired from San Jose in March 1996, had
10 goals and 43 assists for Phoenix last season.
	   In 158 games over 2 1/2 seasons with the Coyotes, he scored 32
goals and had 94 assists.
	   Debrusk, signed by Tampa Bay as a free agent last August after
six seasons with Edmonton, had one goal, two assists and 166
penalty minutes last season.
	   In seven NHL seasons, he has 963 penalty minutes.
