<TEXT>
	   LEON, Spain (AP) _ World Chess Champion Garry Kasparov of Russia
held a one point lead Thursday over the Bulgarian Grand Master
Veselin Topalov on the second day of their experimental
computer-aided chess tournament.
	   Two matches are played each day over the three-day competition
held in this northern Spanish city.
	   In the first game Thursday Kasparov forced the young Bulgarian
playing the white pieces to a draw.
	   Then the Russian made sure he won his own advantage with the
whites in the second game of the day pushing Topalov into a frantic
but in the end futile defense.
