BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY
NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
600 PM AST THU JUN 11 1998

...THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN SAN JUAN PR HAS EXTENDED
   IN TIME THE URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY EFFECTIVE
   UNTIL 700 PM FOR THE INTERIOR AND WEST SECTIONS OF PUERTO RICO
   FROM UTUADO WEST TO ANASCO...MOCA...AGUADA AND RINCON...


DOPPLER RADAR SHOWED SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS CONTINUING ACROSS
THE ADVISORY AREA AS OF 550 PM...WITH MODERATE TO HEAVY RAIN STILL
OCCURRING ACROSS PORTIONS OF UTUADO. RAINFALL ACCUMULATIONS OF 4
TO 6 INCHES SINCE 300 PM ARE ESTIMATED BY THE DOPPLER ACROSS
SECTIONS OF THE ADVISORY AREA. URBAN AND STREAM FLOODING WILL
CONTINUE ACROSS UTUADO..SAN SEBASTIAN..AND ANASCO THROUGH 630 PM
BEFORE DIMINISHING.  OTHER SHOWERS WERE SPREADING NORTHWEST ACROSS
INTERIOR PORTIONS OF HATILLO AND CAMUY.

MOTORISTS AND PEDESTRIANS IN OR PASSING THROUGH THE ADVISORY AREA
...ESPECIALLY ROAD # 2...THIS EVENING SHOULD AVOID CROSSING
FLOODED ROADS...AND ALLOW EXTRA TIME TO REACH THEIR DESTINATIONS.
REMEMBER...CARS CAN EASILY STALL IN THE WATER AND BE CARRIED AWAY
IN ANY CURRENT. PEDESTRIANS ARE ALSO ADVISED TO STAY AWAY FROM
RISING CREEKS...STREAMS...AND OTHER FLOWING BODIES OF WATER.
