<HEADLINE>
Judge orders barge company not to block competitor from landing
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) _ After four days of
testimony, a judge ruled Thursday that Boyson Inc./Ocean Link barge
serivce had unfairly stopped an upstart competitor, Republic Barge
Service, from doing business.
	   Territorial Court Judge Soroya Diase issued an injunction
stopping Boyson from denying access to port facilities at Red Hook
on St. Thomas.
	   During the hearing, Boyson executives admitted setting up a
blockade of 40-foot tractor trailers at Red hook between April 28
and May 4. But operations manager James Boynes said it was done as
a protest against the Port Authority and not to stop Republic from
doing business.
	   In its dispute with the government, Boyson claimed the exclusive
right to use the ramps it had constructed at the barge landing.
</TEXT>
