<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Canada-Quebec Crash,0126 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Five killed in chain-collision near Montreal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MONTREAL (AP) _ A truck-car pileup killed five people and
injured at least three Thursday near Montreal.
	   Tractor-trailer trucks and cars were shoved into each other in a
chain reaction collision on Highway 40, one of the major arteries
leading off the island of Montreal.
	   The crash occurred when a tanker truck loaded with milk was
approaching a traffic jam and collided with another vehicle.
	   Two cars were caught in the truck's undercarriage and were
dragged into the ditch with it, exploding after they crashed off
the road, police said.
	   The accident forced the closure of parts of the highway, which
runs along the north shore of the St. Lawrence River. 	   
</TEXT>
